01:37.113 --> 01:39.572
You are the queenof customer relations.

01:39.614 --> 01:40.447
Client relations.

01:40.447 --> 01:42.113
Right.

01:42.155 --> 01:44.238
I was actually hopingwe could talk.

01:44.280 --> 01:45.697
Talk?

01:45.739 --> 01:47.822
Yeah.About us?

01:47.864 --> 01:50.405
The where-are-we-goingconversation.

01:50.447 --> 01:51.781
Part...five.

01:51.781 --> 01:53.155
Yes, of coursewe can talk,

01:53.197 --> 01:55.614
but right now,I really have to go.

01:55.656 --> 01:57.614
Um, what about dinner?

01:57.656 --> 01:59.447
What aboutChameleons at 7:00?

01:59.489 --> 02:01.072
Perfect. Wish me luck.

02:01.948 --> 02:02.781
Luck.

02:03.822 --> 02:05.697
[knocking]Mr. St. Clair?

02:05.739 --> 02:07.447
Ms. Quinn, come in.

02:10.864 --> 02:12.113
How can I help you?

02:12.155 --> 02:14.364
Please, have a seat.

02:15.197 --> 02:17.072
I have heardnothing but good things

02:17.113 --> 02:19.322
about your performancein Client Relations.

02:19.364 --> 02:21.155
Thank you.

02:21.197 --> 02:23.405
That's whyI wanted to see you.

02:23.447 --> 02:25.113
I've read your resume,

02:25.113 --> 02:27.072
and I see you've studiedarchitecture at Duke.

02:27.113 --> 02:28.781
Yes, I've wantedto design things

02:28.822 --> 02:30.322
ever since I was a little girl.

02:30.364 --> 02:33.113
Hmm, and yet you're stillin client relations.

02:33.155 --> 02:36.656
Well, I'm just waitingon my door to open.

02:36.697 --> 02:39.572
Why don't we seeif we can kick that door down?

02:41.781 --> 02:42.614
I don't follow.

02:42.656 --> 02:43.948
Well, due toa scheduling change,

02:43.989 --> 02:46.948
the Sapphire Lake projectis now slated to break ground

02:46.948 --> 02:49.030
in less than 30 days.

02:49.072 --> 02:50.197
Sapphire Lake?

02:50.238 --> 02:51.697
Oh, yes, of course,you wouldn't know about it.

02:51.739 --> 02:53.614
We are getting ready to builda new retail development

02:53.614 --> 02:54.530
at Sapphire Lake.

02:54.572 --> 02:57.030
However, I find myselfin a dilemma,

02:57.072 --> 02:58.656
thanks toa 60-something-year-old woman

02:58.697 --> 02:59.781
who refusesto sell us her property,

02:59.822 --> 03:00.906
land that is

03:00.948 --> 03:02.822
smack-dab in the centerof our new development.

03:02.864 --> 03:05.948
Now, I need someonewith people skills, Ms. Quinn,

03:05.948 --> 03:07.155
and that's whereyou come in.

03:07.197 --> 03:08.280
My assistant hasmentioned to me

03:08.322 --> 03:10.155
that you grew upnear Sapphire Lake?

03:10.197 --> 03:12.364
Yes. I've spenta lot of time there.

03:12.405 --> 03:14.155
It's one of my favorite places.

03:14.197 --> 03:15.197
Good. Come with me.

03:23.614 --> 03:25.155
Watch this.

03:26.447 --> 03:28.656
[video]: Welcome to Sapphire Lake,

03:28.697 --> 03:30.155
Stoneland Properties' newest

03:30.197 --> 03:32.656
luxury housing and retail space,

03:32.697 --> 03:35.614
relaxing small-town living meets the convenience...

03:35.656 --> 03:36.781
[man's voice]: I sure hope Mrs. Figgins

03:36.781 --> 03:38.364
never cuts down our tree.

03:39.614 --> 03:41.781
Maybe you shouldcheck the knothole.

03:41.822 --> 03:44.238
If I do, will youstop acting so weird?

03:44.280 --> 03:45.697
Maybe.

03:45.739 --> 03:46.989
[chuckles]

03:47.948 --> 03:49.113
Hey, you know I kept

03:49.155 --> 03:50.656
all those notes and lettersyou sent me, right?

03:50.697 --> 03:51.781
Megan, wait.

03:53.280 --> 03:56.322
Joe, do you want me to checkin the knothole or not?

03:56.364 --> 03:58.322
Yes.

03:58.364 --> 04:00.906
But first...

04:04.405 --> 04:05.322
Megan,

04:05.364 --> 04:07.364
we've known each otherour whole lives,

04:07.405 --> 04:12.031
from preschoolto high school graduation,

04:12.072 --> 04:14.322
but I don't want to talkabout the past.

04:14.364 --> 04:17.031
I want to talkabout the future.

04:17.072 --> 04:19.279
[voice echoes] The future.

04:19.279 --> 04:21.697
[video]: ...making waking up tomorrow

04:21.738 --> 04:22.906
better today.

04:22.948 --> 04:25.238
Voilà!

04:26.739 --> 04:27.822
Wow.

04:27.864 --> 04:29.572
I hardly recognize it.

04:29.614 --> 04:30.822
Impressive, isn't it?

04:30.864 --> 04:32.113
Yes, it is.

04:32.113 --> 04:34.280
Stick with me on this, Quinn.

04:41.405 --> 04:42.447
Mr. St. Clair,

04:42.489 --> 04:44.948
I'm not certain Sapphire Lakeis the best place

04:44.948 --> 04:46.614
for a development like that.

04:46.656 --> 04:48.656
Well, according toour market research, it is.

04:48.697 --> 04:50.572
However this woman,Frances Figgins,

04:50.614 --> 04:51.864
is holding upthe whole project.

04:51.906 --> 04:54.614
We need her parcel of land,and she refuses to sell.

04:54.614 --> 04:56.781
She's really the last obstaclein our way,

04:56.822 --> 04:59.072
and despite my best effortsto reason with her,

04:59.113 --> 05:00.072
she has now hung up on me--

05:00.113 --> 05:02.239
now, let me think...six times?

05:02.280 --> 05:03.405
Seven times, sir.

05:03.447 --> 05:05.781
Seven times.

05:05.781 --> 05:08.113
I'm not sure if you've beento Sapphire Lake,

05:08.113 --> 05:08.948
but it really is

05:08.989 --> 05:11.489
a very tranquiland, and--

05:11.530 --> 05:14.031
Let me stop youright there, Ms. Quinn.

05:14.072 --> 05:15.948
Would you like to getout of client relations

05:15.948 --> 05:17.447
and one day design

05:17.447 --> 05:19.280
a Stoneland Propertiesdevelopment?

05:19.322 --> 05:20.113
Of course.

05:20.155 --> 05:21.280
Then you needto learn

05:21.322 --> 05:22.781
that sentimentalityand business don't mix.

05:22.822 --> 05:25.197
Now, Sapphire Lakeis going to be

05:25.238 --> 05:26.656
our biggest development to date,

05:26.697 --> 05:28.489
and our CEO wants to make surethat everything goes smoothly.

05:28.530 --> 05:30.614
The very futureof this division

05:30.614 --> 05:31.614
depends on it.

05:31.656 --> 05:32.864
Now, it's been broughtto my attention

05:32.906 --> 05:34.530
that you are quitea people person,

05:34.572 --> 05:36.031
which is why I thinkyou're the best person

05:36.072 --> 05:37.614
to help usclose this deal.

05:37.614 --> 05:39.031
So, are you in?

05:43.948 --> 05:44.822
I'm in.

05:45.697 --> 05:47.113
Good.I'm counting on you.

05:47.113 --> 05:48.614
Is my car ready?

05:48.656 --> 05:49.614
Waitingfor you, sir.

05:49.614 --> 05:50.781
Wonderful.

05:50.781 --> 05:52.530
Now, you have to getMrs. Figgins to agree to sell

05:52.572 --> 05:54.280
before we're forced to paythe contractors a penalty.

05:54.280 --> 05:55.906
If that happens,

05:55.948 --> 05:58.364
the board of directorswill pull the plug,

05:58.405 --> 06:00.031
and let me assure you,Ms. Quinn,

06:00.072 --> 06:01.405
that will notbe a good thing.

06:01.447 --> 06:02.572
Not for any of us.

06:02.614 --> 06:03.572
Now, you've got till Monday

06:03.614 --> 06:04.739
at 10:00 a.m.

06:04.781 --> 06:06.031
to close the deal.

06:06.072 --> 06:07.739
You do that,and I'll personally see to it

06:07.781 --> 06:09.989
that you get a shotat your dream.

06:11.656 --> 06:12.614
I'm sorry,

06:12.656 --> 06:15.322
did you say, uh,Monday morning?

06:15.364 --> 06:17.572
As in four days from now?

06:17.614 --> 06:18.530
That's right.

06:18.572 --> 06:19.864
We're all counting on you.

06:19.906 --> 06:21.155
Don't let us down.

06:27.864 --> 06:30.530
[♪♪]

06:34.364 --> 06:36.614
So, I guess youhaven't seen it?

06:36.656 --> 06:38.697
Seen what?

06:38.739 --> 06:42.031
The latest editionof Chicago Attorney.

06:42.072 --> 06:42.864
[chuckles]

06:42.906 --> 06:43.697
No, I haven't.

06:43.739 --> 06:45.864
I dog-eared the page.

06:45.906 --> 06:47.280
"Meet Chicago's

06:47.280 --> 06:50.572
ten fastest risinglegal stars..."

06:53.322 --> 06:54.697
"Number seven...

06:54.739 --> 06:56.489
Philip Allen Carter."

06:56.530 --> 06:57.864
Wow, Philip,

06:57.906 --> 06:59.113
this is amazing.

06:59.155 --> 07:00.697
I love that they usedmy full name.

07:00.739 --> 07:01.739
Wow, I am so proud of you.

07:01.781 --> 07:02.906
Thank you.

07:02.948 --> 07:06.280
I actually had someonerecognize me at lunch today.

07:06.280 --> 07:07.822
It was... surreal.

07:07.864 --> 07:11.113
I knew all your hard workand long hours would pay off.

07:11.155 --> 07:12.906
Well, you know, I figuredit's not just good for me,

07:12.948 --> 07:14.447
it's good for us.

07:14.447 --> 07:15.614
[snapping fingers]

07:15.614 --> 07:17.239
Wine list?

07:18.739 --> 07:20.697
Good for us?

07:20.739 --> 07:21.781
Yeah.

07:21.822 --> 07:23.948
Now that my career's taking off,

07:23.989 --> 07:26.280
I was hoping we could talkabout our future.

07:27.822 --> 07:30.572
Oh, okay.

07:30.614 --> 07:33.989
Um... you know, Philip,

07:34.031 --> 07:34.989
I'm just really focused

07:35.031 --> 07:37.572
on this Sapphire Lake thingfor work.

07:37.614 --> 07:38.948
Maybe we could wait--

07:38.989 --> 07:40.031
Megan...

07:40.072 --> 07:41.822
We've been waiting.

07:41.864 --> 07:43.364
We've been dating, what,

07:43.405 --> 07:44.697
nine months?

07:44.739 --> 07:46.322
I haven't metyour family yet.

07:46.364 --> 07:48.239
Why haven't you invited mehome to Cedarville?

07:49.280 --> 07:50.280
Vale.

07:50.280 --> 07:53.072
It's Cedarvale.

07:54.155 --> 07:56.656
We've been working so much,

07:56.697 --> 07:57.864
both of us.

07:57.906 --> 07:58.906
Is it that,

07:58.948 --> 08:01.280
or is that you'rejust not sure about me?

08:02.614 --> 08:04.489
No, it is... it's not you.

08:04.530 --> 08:06.364
I just, I just need--

08:06.405 --> 08:08.197
"A little more time."

08:08.238 --> 08:09.405
Right?

08:09.447 --> 08:11.781
That's what you sayevery time I bring this up.

08:13.364 --> 08:14.405
Megan...

08:14.447 --> 08:15.781
I'm a catch.

08:15.822 --> 08:17.489
I know you are.

08:17.530 --> 08:19.031
[cell phone rings]

08:19.072 --> 08:20.530
Oh.

08:21.989 --> 08:24.656
It's the CedarvaleHospital.

08:24.697 --> 08:25.781
I need to take this.

08:25.822 --> 08:26.822
Sure.

08:26.864 --> 08:29.113
Megan Quinn.

08:29.155 --> 08:31.113
Hello, Dr. Baker.

08:31.155 --> 08:32.155
Is everything okay?

08:33.197 --> 08:34.948
Oh.

08:34.948 --> 08:35.948
Okay.

08:35.989 --> 08:37.780
Thanks for calling.

08:37.822 --> 08:38.864
Uh, yes.

08:38.905 --> 08:40.697
I can be therefirst thing in the morning.

08:40.739 --> 08:42.905
Goodbye,Dr. Baker.

08:42.948 --> 08:44.030
What is it?

08:44.072 --> 08:46.864
My dad fell off a ladderand fractured his foot.

08:46.906 --> 08:48.530
He's spending the nightin the hospital.

08:48.572 --> 08:51.280
Well, doesn't soundtoo serious. Right?

08:51.322 --> 08:52.197
I can'tmiss my flight

08:52.239 --> 08:53.280
if I'm goingto see my dad

08:53.322 --> 08:55.113
before I meetwith Mrs. Figgins.

08:55.155 --> 08:56.572
So...

08:56.614 --> 08:57.948
where does that leave us?

08:57.948 --> 08:59.447
I promise

08:59.489 --> 09:01.405
I'm going to thinkeverything over.

09:01.447 --> 09:02.405
Fine.

09:02.447 --> 09:03.405
But remember,

09:03.447 --> 09:05.948
the number sevenfastest rising legal star

09:05.948 --> 09:07.364
in Chicago

09:07.405 --> 09:08.906
is not gonna beon the market for long.

09:08.948 --> 09:10.155
I'll think fast.

09:11.031 --> 09:11.781
I'll call you.

09:11.822 --> 09:12.739
Have a safe trip.

09:12.781 --> 09:13.656
Okay, thanks,

09:13.697 --> 09:15.364
and congratulations.

09:16.530 --> 09:18.864
[♪♪]

10:07.781 --> 10:09.155
Dad?

10:09.197 --> 10:11.322
Mom?

10:12.530 --> 10:13.697
What?

10:14.989 --> 10:16.822
Your fatherwanted to surprise you.

10:16.864 --> 10:18.073
Surprise me?

10:18.113 --> 10:18.948
Honey,

10:18.989 --> 10:21.906
I've got some terrific news!

10:21.948 --> 10:23.948
You are--

10:23.948 --> 10:25.572
--going to bea Duke Blue Devil!

10:25.614 --> 10:27.322
Violet!

10:27.364 --> 10:28.697
[applause]

10:28.739 --> 10:29.739
Congratulations, honey.

10:29.781 --> 10:30.530
-Really?-Yes!

10:30.572 --> 10:31.781
I...

