It was pure chaos.

14:14.447 --> 14:15.489
Waitresscalled in sick again.

14:15.530 --> 14:18.530
I knew it,I knew it!

14:18.572 --> 14:20.031
I gotta getback to work.

14:21.073 --> 14:23.447
Can you pull some stringsand get me out of here?

14:23.489 --> 14:25.113
Hey! I heard that.

14:25.155 --> 14:26.781
Oh boy.

14:26.822 --> 14:27.948
Gotta run.

14:27.989 --> 14:29.073
Meet up later at the café?

14:29.113 --> 14:30.405
Yeah, sounds good.

14:30.447 --> 14:31.280
And stay away

14:31.280 --> 14:32.614
from those oldladders, Mr. Q.

14:32.614 --> 14:34.239
I will try.

14:34.280 --> 14:36.447
How's my favoritepatient today?

14:36.447 --> 14:39.322
Oh, you know, could be better,could be worse.

14:39.364 --> 14:40.614
I was speaking to Megan.

14:42.322 --> 14:43.447
[chuckles]

14:43.489 --> 14:45.489
Aw, hey,Dr. Baker.

14:45.530 --> 14:46.864
You are looking moreand more like your mother

14:46.906 --> 14:47.906
every time I see you.

14:47.948 --> 14:49.239
Well, thank you.

14:49.280 --> 14:50.572
I can't thinkof a better compliment.

14:51.447 --> 14:53.073
Um, so, is hegoing to be okay?

14:53.113 --> 14:54.322
Yeah, he'll be all right.

14:54.364 --> 14:56.280
Okay, then,when can I get out of here?

14:56.322 --> 14:58.697
I mean, come on,it's Apple Festival Week.

14:58.739 --> 15:00.280
It's my big profit time.

15:00.322 --> 15:02.781
Apparently, my businessis falling apart.

15:02.781 --> 15:04.739
Well, you cango home today if you want.

15:04.781 --> 15:05.781
Well, about time.

15:05.822 --> 15:07.155
Of course, you needto stay off your feet

15:07.197 --> 15:08.989
for a little while,

15:09.031 --> 15:10.155
and out of the café.

15:10.197 --> 15:11.405
Oh, no, no, no,I can't do that.

15:11.447 --> 15:12.656
I've gota business to run.

15:12.697 --> 15:14.530
Okay, I guess we cankeep him here

15:14.572 --> 15:16.031
a little while longer?

15:18.697 --> 15:20.739
Okay, fine,

15:20.781 --> 15:21.864
you win.

15:21.906 --> 15:23.572
You need to letyour foot heal properly

15:23.614 --> 15:25.781
before you returnto work, okay?

15:25.781 --> 15:27.614
And if I hear you've beenback in that café too soon,

15:27.614 --> 15:29.073
you'll have me to answer to.

15:29.114 --> 15:30.114
You understand?

15:30.114 --> 15:31.948
[sighing heavily]Yes, I understand.

15:31.948 --> 15:34.864
Megan, you make surehe keeps his promise.

15:34.906 --> 15:35.989
Will do, Doctor.

15:36.031 --> 15:37.322
-Okay.-Thank you.

15:40.447 --> 15:41.781
Okay, I've gotto pack up my things.

15:41.822 --> 15:43.906
I need to get downto the café as soon as possible.

15:43.948 --> 15:47.114
Dad, no, did you hearwhat he just said?

15:47.114 --> 15:49.073
[grumbles dismissively]Ah, doctor talk.

15:49.114 --> 15:50.405
No, I'm fine.

15:50.447 --> 15:51.614
I can do more on one foot

15:51.614 --> 15:53.238
than most folkscould do on three.

15:53.280 --> 15:55.781
Dad, you can't rush things,

15:55.822 --> 15:57.155
or elseit'll make it worse.

15:57.197 --> 15:59.114
Well, what do youexpect me to do?

15:59.114 --> 16:01.031
Burn the place down?

16:03.280 --> 16:05.864
Or...

16:05.906 --> 16:07.781
Or you could, uh...

16:07.822 --> 16:10.614
you could work with mefor a while.

16:10.656 --> 16:12.781
No. No, no, Dad, no,

16:12.781 --> 16:13.781
I cannot do that.

16:13.822 --> 16:14.948
[sighing] Well...

16:14.948 --> 16:17.989
I guess I'll justhave to call Dottie, and...

16:18.031 --> 16:20.031
have her shut it down.

16:23.238 --> 16:24.948
Okay, I will help out.

16:24.948 --> 16:26.114
Are you sureyou can handle it?

16:26.155 --> 16:29.822
Dad, I've done every jobpossible at Rosie's.

16:29.864 --> 16:31.530
[cell phone rings]How hard can it be?

16:33.697 --> 16:34.781
I've justgot to get this.

16:34.822 --> 16:36.280
One sec.

16:37.781 --> 16:38.781
Megan Quinn.

16:38.822 --> 16:39.989
Are you with Mrs. Figgins?

16:40.031 --> 16:40.989
Yes.

16:41.031 --> 16:41.948
I mean, no.

16:41.948 --> 16:43.781
I mean,I'm on my way there

16:43.781 --> 16:45.656
right now.-Good.

16:45.697 --> 16:46.989
With what we're offering her,she should be begging us,

16:47.031 --> 16:48.155
and not the other way around.

16:48.197 --> 16:49.489
Now, your job is to convince her

16:49.530 --> 16:51.656
that this deal is in her best interest.

16:51.697 --> 16:52.822
Oh, and, Ms. Quinn?

16:52.864 --> 16:54.405
Yes, Mr. St. Clair?

16:54.447 --> 16:55.781
The clock is ticking.

16:57.614 --> 16:59.073
Uh...

16:59.114 --> 17:00.697
[beeps off]

17:00.739 --> 17:03.197
[♪♪]

17:13.446 --> 17:15.571
[trowel scraping]

17:22.364 --> 17:23.196
Mrs. Figgins?

17:25.739 --> 17:26.739
May I help you?

17:26.781 --> 17:28.864
Hi. I hope you remember me.

17:28.906 --> 17:30.572
It's beena long time.

17:30.614 --> 17:32.197
[gasps in delight]Megan Quinn.

17:32.238 --> 17:36.864
Oh, my goodness, look at you.

17:38.405 --> 17:40.572
Oh, I always knew

17:40.614 --> 17:42.948
you'd grow up to bea beautiful woman.

17:42.989 --> 17:45.073
Thank you.

17:45.114 --> 17:47.948
To what do I owethis pleasure?

17:47.948 --> 17:50.197
Well, I was just in townvisiting my dad,

17:50.238 --> 17:52.238
and I thoughtI'd stop by and say hi.

17:52.280 --> 17:53.906
Oh, yes,that's right.

17:53.948 --> 17:55.948
I heard Mattwas in the hospital.

17:55.948 --> 17:57.155
Now, how's he doing?

17:57.197 --> 17:58.948
Oh, he's fine,thank you.

17:58.948 --> 18:00.114
He just fractured his foot.

18:00.155 --> 18:02.822
Oh dear, that sounds painful.

18:02.864 --> 18:03.906
Please,

18:03.948 --> 18:05.239
give him my best.

18:05.280 --> 18:06.822
I will.

18:06.864 --> 18:09.073
Have you seen Joe?

18:09.114 --> 18:12.239
He's backin town, you know.

18:12.280 --> 18:15.572
I bumped into him earlier.

18:15.614 --> 18:16.614
Once upon a time,

18:16.614 --> 18:19.864
you two were liketwo peas in a pod.

18:19.906 --> 18:22.114
But I guesstimes change, huh?

18:22.114 --> 18:24.781
Yes.

18:24.781 --> 18:26.447
Uh, Mrs. Figgins...

18:26.447 --> 18:30.073
Oh, please, call me Frances.

18:30.114 --> 18:32.280
I mean, you'reall grown up now.

18:32.322 --> 18:33.614
I think you can usemy given name.

18:33.614 --> 18:35.447
Okay. Frances...

18:35.489 --> 18:36.614
[chuckles fondly]

18:36.656 --> 18:39.614
Uh, Frances, I hopeyou don't think I'm intruding.

18:39.656 --> 18:41.489
I rang the doorbell,but no one came, so--

18:41.530 --> 18:43.572
Oh, listen,it's no intrusion.

18:43.614 --> 18:45.739
As a matter of fact,it's a nice diversion.

18:45.781 --> 18:46.697
When the doorbell rang,

18:46.739 --> 18:48.322
I thought you were one of them.

18:49.280 --> 18:50.781
"Them"?

18:50.781 --> 18:52.614
Those horrible developers.

18:52.614 --> 18:54.614
Did you know thatthere's this company

18:54.656 --> 18:56.073
trying to buy up my home

18:56.114 --> 18:57.447
and turn it intoa shopping mall?

18:57.447 --> 18:59.114
They think they canjust throw money at me,

18:59.114 --> 19:01.447
and I'll hand over my propertywithout a thought

19:01.489 --> 19:03.239
as to how they intendto use the land.

19:05.114 --> 19:06.280
Anyway...

19:06.322 --> 19:10.031
Megan, it's so good to see you.

19:10.073 --> 19:12.197
I mean, what are you doingthese days?

19:12.239 --> 19:14.364
Uh... well,

19:14.405 --> 19:16.822
I work at Stoneland Properties.

19:16.864 --> 19:18.864
I'm in clientrelations.

19:21.197 --> 19:23.572
Um, I know you'vespoken to my boss

19:23.614 --> 19:24.781
several times,

19:24.781 --> 19:26.781
Jordan St. Clair,

19:26.781 --> 19:28.280
but he wanted meto come here

19:28.322 --> 19:30.155
and personallytake you through--

19:30.197 --> 19:32.280
Ms. Quinn...

19:32.322 --> 19:34.364
We reallyfeel like this development

19:34.405 --> 19:36.948
is gonna energizethe local economy

19:36.948 --> 19:39.822
and create hundreds ofgreat new jobs for people--

19:39.864 --> 19:40.989
Ms. Quinn.

19:41.031 --> 19:43.280
Please, just call me Megan.

19:43.280 --> 19:44.781
Ms. Quinn.

19:44.822 --> 19:46.989
I am not interested.

19:49.530 --> 19:52.322
Listen, I understand

19:52.364 --> 19:54.073
if you arereluctant to sell.

19:54.114 --> 19:55.031
I mean, look at this place.

19:55.073 --> 19:57.530
Reluctantto sell?

19:57.572 --> 19:59.614
Actually,it's quite the opposite.

19:59.656 --> 20:02.031
I have been planning to sellfor some time.

20:02.073 --> 20:03.906
I mean,I'm getting older,

20:03.948 --> 20:05.073
and pretty soon

20:05.114 --> 20:07.906
this place is gonna becometoo much for me.

20:07.948 --> 20:10.781
I had plannedto put my house on the market

20:10.781 --> 20:12.447
and move to Florida

20:12.447 --> 20:14.364
and live with my daughterand my grandchildren.

20:14.405 --> 20:16.948
If I sell to you,

20:16.989 --> 20:18.614
I will be responsible

20:18.656 --> 20:21.322
for this monstrosityof asphalt and cement

20:21.364 --> 20:23.572
that they're proposing.

20:23.614 --> 20:25.447
I couldn't live with myself.

20:26.322 --> 20:28.447
So, have youseen the plans?

20:28.489 --> 20:30.073
Of course I have,

20:30.114 --> 20:31.781
and the localplanning commission

20:31.781 --> 20:33.280
will never approvethe development

20:33.322 --> 20:34.989
as long as I ownthis property.

20:35.822 --> 20:37.530
Planning commission?

20:37.572 --> 20:38.989
I sent them overa basket

20:39.031 --> 20:40.906
of my freshly bakedpumpkin muffins

20:40.948 --> 20:42.614
at their last meeting.

20:42.614 --> 20:45.197
They said they were delicious.

20:45.238 --> 20:50.280
So, it looks like I holdall the cards, Ms. Quinn.

20:50.280 --> 20:51.364
Good day.

20:51.405 --> 20:52.489
Frances, if I could just--

20:52.530 --> 20:55.572
Please, it's, it's,it's Mrs. Figgins,

20:55.614 --> 20:58.822
and this conversation is over.

21:00.989 --> 21:02.614
What happened to you?

21:02.656 --> 21:06.572
To the girl thatI used to know?

21:06.614 --> 21:09.656
You were going to dogreat things.

21:15.364 --> 21:17.948
[door closes]

21:17.948 --> 21:20.656
[♪♪]

21:27.656 --> 21:29.614
[sighs]

21:37.781 --> 21:40.114
[Chloe]: How'd it go with Mrs... What's her name?

21:40.156 --> 21:42.031
So far, she's not budging.

21:42.073 --> 21:44.239
Oh, all you needed...

21:44.280 --> 21:45.447
That's not good.

21:45.447 --> 21:47.989
No, it's not.

21:48.031 --> 21:49.364
Sorry it didn't go well.

21:49.405 --> 21:54.530
And to make matters worse,my ex is back in town.

21:54.572 --> 21:55.948
Oh, wow.

21:55.989 --> 21:57.447
Your ex?

21:57.447 --> 21:59.073
Please elaborate.

21:59.114 --> 22:01.614
Well, to make a very long story short,

22:01.656 --> 22:03.989
his name's Joe.

22:04.031 --> 22:05.322
We grew up together,

22:05.364 --> 22:07.447
dated all through high school,

22:07.447 --> 22:09.948
and then, a week intomy freshman year of college,

22:09.948 --> 22:11.948
he sent me a letterbreaking up with me,

22:11.948 --> 22:14.614
said we'd grown apart, whatever that means.

22:14.656 --> 22:16.530
Then, when I tried to call him,

22:16.572 --> 22:18.489
he wouldn't take my calls.

22:18.530 --> 22:20.530
That had to sting.

22:20.572 --> 22:22.614
So, whatever happened to him?

22:22.614 --> 22:24.114
He moved away,

22:24.114 --> 22:25.864
met someone, got married,

22:25.906 --> 22:28.156
had a baby girl.

22:28.197 --> 22:30.197
Actually, his wife passed away.

22:30.238 --> 22:32.239
How sad.

22:32.280 --> 22:33.156
Yeah.

22:33.197 --> 22:36.156
He's been a single dadever since.

22:36.197 --> 22:37.906
And just when I thought

22:37.948 --> 22:40.322
I'd probably neversee him again,

22:40.364 --> 22:42.197
I ran into him today.

22:42.239 --> 22:43.280
Literally.

22:43.280 --> 22:45.739
I ran into his pickup truck.

22:45.781 --> 22:47.739
[chuckles] Ouch.

22:47.781 --> 22:49.197
Ah, sweet freedom!

22:49.238 --> 22:52.405
Ha ha!Now I can get some real food.

22:52.447 --> 22:53.989
Oh, hey, honey!

22:54.031 --> 22:55.530
Chloe, I gotta go.

22:55.572 --> 22:56.530
I'll call you back.

22:58.364 --> 23:00.989
[♪♪]

23:04.447 --> 23:06.197
[sighing]

23:06.238 --> 23:07.280
Oof.

23:07.322 --> 23:09.073
I got you.

23:09.114 --> 23:10.156
Aw, thanks, darling.

23:10.197 --> 23:11.197
No problem.

23:15.572 --> 23:16.781
Lunch is served.

23:16.822 --> 23:18.156
Excellent.

23:20.948 --> 23:23.239
Um... there's...there's no meat.

23:23.280 --> 23:26.656
We're eating healthytoday, Dad.

23:28.781 --> 23:30.572
So...

23:30.614 --> 23:32.280
how are you feeling?

23:33.572 --> 23:35.614
I'm fine.

23:35.614 --> 23:37.572
I don't need a babysitter.

23:37.614 --> 23:38.656
I know you don't.

23:38.697 --> 23:40.114
[cell phone rings]

23:41.781 --> 23:43.906
Megan Quinn.

23:43.948 --> 23:47.364
So, how did your meetingwith Mrs. Figgins go?

23:47.405 --> 23:49.405
It went...

23:49.447 --> 23:50.447
really well.

23:50.489 --> 23:53.238
Yes, well, I was waiting for an update.

23:53.280 --> 23:55.197
Yeah, I was just aboutto call you.

23:55.238 --> 23:57.238
The reception'sreally spotty here.

23:57.280 --> 23:58.739
You know, small towns.

23:58.781 --> 23:59.697
Hmm.

23:59.739 --> 24:00.948
So, you'll havegood news for me soon?

24:00.989 --> 24:02.572
Yes, I will.

24:02.614 --> 24:03.906
We're very close.

24:03.948 --> 24:05.447
That's whatI like to hear, Ms. Quinn.

24:05.489 --> 24:08.114
You call me as soon as youhave the signed documents.

24:08.114 --> 24:09.197
Will do.

24:11.989 --> 24:13.238
What was that all about?

24:15.447 --> 24:16.781
Can I trust younot to overdo it

24:16.822 --> 24:18.114
if I head out for a little bit?

24:18.156 --> 24:19.781
Of course.

24:19.822 --> 24:23.280
Like I said,I don't need a babysitter.

24:23.280 --> 24:24.447
Okay.

24:24.447 --> 24:26.948
Are you going to go seeFrances Figgins again?

24:26.989 --> 24:28.781
How do you know about that?

24:28.822 --> 24:31.156
You know, small town.

24:32.656 --> 24:34.614
Call me if you need anything.

24:34.614 --> 24:35.489
All right.

24:35.530 --> 24:37.948
Oh, before you gosee Frances again,

24:37.948 --> 24:38.948
can you stop by Rosie's

24:38.948 --> 24:41.697
and make sureeverything's okay?

24:41.739 --> 24:43.781
It'll just make me feel better.

24:43.822 --> 24:45.447
Sure, Dad.

24:46.739 --> 24:47.614
I'll call you.

24:47.656 --> 24:49.197
Okay.

24:57.197 --> 24:58.405
Hello.

24:58.447 --> 25:00.114
Hi.

25:00.114 --> 25:01.280
What's your name?

25:01.280 --> 25:03.114
My name's Megan.What's your name?

25:03.114 --> 25:05.073
Hurry up,slowpoke.

25:05.114 --> 25:06.614
Okay, okay.

25:06.614 --> 25:09.114
You're too fast for me.

25:09.114 --> 25:10.280
Hello.

25:10.322 --> 25:11.614
Hello.

25:11.614 --> 25:12.489
Again.

25:12.530 --> 25:14.822
Do you know her, Daddy?

25:15.781 --> 25:16.989
I do.

25:17.948 --> 25:19.864
You must be Lily.

25:19.906 --> 25:20.822
How do you know my name?

25:20.864 --> 25:22.447
I've heard about you.

25:22.447 --> 25:25.447
Megan and I knew each otherwhen we were your age.

25:25.489 --> 25:27.031
Wow, that's a long time ago.

25:27.073 --> 25:27.989
[chuckles]

25:28.031 --> 25:29.280
You know, Lily,

25:29.322 --> 25:30.197
when your dad and I were little,

25:30.238 --> 25:31.572
we used to ride bikes together.

25:31.614 --> 25:33.073
-Really?-Mm-hm.

25:33.114 --> 25:34.781
Do you want to comebike riding with us?

25:34.822 --> 25:35.656
[laughs]

25:36.697 --> 25:38.739
Um, I'd love to,

25:38.781 --> 25:40.489
but I'm headingover to the café.

25:40.530 --> 25:43.031
I'm helping outwhile my dad's laid up.

25:43.073 --> 25:44.405
You mean Rosie's café?

25:44.447 --> 25:45.906
That's the one.

25:45.948 --> 25:47.197
Megan's family owns Rosie's.

25:47.239 --> 25:49.280
I want to go.Can we, Daddy?

25:50.197 --> 25:51.989
Um...

25:54.948 --> 25:57.614
Well, yeah, we couldhead over there in a bit.

25:57.614 --> 25:59.073
Yes!

25:59.114 --> 26:00.822
Well, it was nicemeeting you, Lily.

26:00.864 --> 26:02.364
Maybe I'll see you later.

26:02.405 --> 26:03.781
Okay.

26:03.822 --> 26:04.864
Bye, Megan.

26:04.906 --> 26:05.906
Bye.

26:09.114 --> 26:10.572
Bye.

26:10.614 --> 26:12.322
Goodbye.

26:29.989 --> 26:32.405
Hey, Dottie.

26:32.447 --> 26:33.572
Megan!

26:33.614 --> 26:35.198
Oh!

26:35.239 --> 26:39.572
Oh, you are a sightfor sore eyes, girl.

26:39.614 --> 26:41.739
I've actually got to getto an important meeting,

26:41.781 --> 26:43.656
but my dad said to stop by,I told him I would,

26:43.697 --> 26:45.364
make sureeverything's okay.

26:45.405 --> 26:46.572
Mm, follow me.

26:47.781 --> 26:49.280
I actually gottaget going.

26:49.322 --> 26:50.614
Our extra waitress

26:50.614 --> 26:52.447
for the festival crowddidn't show up,

26:52.447 --> 26:53.948
and I am swamped,

26:53.948 --> 26:55.280
and I just spoke to Matt,and he said

26:55.322 --> 26:56.781
you'd be willingto help out.

26:56.781 --> 26:58.572
But I...

27:00.280 --> 27:01.405
Wait, you want meto wait tables?

27:01.447 --> 27:02.781
That's the general idea.

27:02.781 --> 27:05.781
Dottie, I haven'twaited tables in years,

27:05.781 --> 27:08.447
and I'm already latefor my meeting.

27:08.447 --> 27:09.948
Hmm, well, Matt said thatif you wouldn't do it

27:09.948 --> 27:11.280
to give him a call,

27:11.280 --> 27:13.405
and he'd be in the next cabdown here to do it himself.

27:22.280 --> 27:23.364
[sighing]

27:28.697 --> 27:29.656
I'm really sorry.

27:31.239 --> 27:32.906
...just clean that up...

27:39.156 --> 27:40.280
[sighs]

27:43.447 --> 27:44.364
All right.

27:47.156 --> 27:48.322
More coffee, right?

27:48.364 --> 27:50.614
And I'll get you guysyour check, and--

27:50.614 --> 27:51.405
[sighs]

27:51.447 --> 27:53.073
Hi.

27:53.114 --> 27:54.114
Hey.

27:54.156 --> 27:55.156
Hi, Megan.

27:55.198 --> 27:56.114
Hi, Lily.

27:56.156 --> 27:57.156
You're a waitress?

27:57.198 --> 27:59.781
Uh, yeah, sort of.

27:59.822 --> 28:01.280
Uh, hey, Lily,how would you like to help me?

28:01.322 --> 28:02.822
Really?

28:02.864 --> 28:04.822
If it's okay with your dad.

28:04.864 --> 28:06.864
Can I, Daddy? Please?

28:06.906 --> 28:08.614
Uh...

28:08.614 --> 28:09.822
Yeah, sure, sweetie,why not?

28:09.864 --> 28:11.614
All right,let's get you an apron.

28:11.656 --> 28:12.906
Come on.

28:17.405 --> 28:18.697
Whoa.

28:18.739 --> 28:20.572
[♪♪]

28:20.614 --> 28:22.156
Okay, good job.

28:22.198 --> 28:23.697
Let's do thesilverware.

28:23.739 --> 28:24.989
[Lily]: Okay!

28:26.614 --> 28:27.489
Okay...

28:27.530 --> 28:29.322
[♪♪]

28:29.364 --> 28:30.239
[Lily]: Uh-huh.

28:34.198 --> 28:35.114
Napkins...

28:35.156 --> 28:36.489
[Lily]: Sure!

28:38.114 --> 28:41.989
I think Lily wasborn to wait tables.

28:42.031 --> 28:43.031
[chuckles]

28:43.073 --> 28:45.697
Seems so.

28:53.614 --> 28:54.489
[clears throat]

28:55.614 --> 28:57.447
Is, uh...

28:57.447 --> 29:00.364
is somethingon your mind, Dottie?

29:00.405 --> 29:02.822
You broke her heart, Joe.

29:02.864 --> 29:03.989
Just thoughtyou should know that.

29:08.781 --> 29:10.364
Okay.

29:11.447 --> 29:12.906
Thanks for letting me know.

29:12.948 --> 29:14.781
You're welcome.

29:17.781 --> 29:21.031
[♪♪]

29:41.656 --> 29:44.739
[♪♪]

29:52.530 --> 29:53.614
No, no, no, I think

29:53.656 --> 29:55.614
I have to havea little bit of this.

29:55.656 --> 29:57.280
We need totake that away.

29:57.322 --> 29:58.447
How cozy.

29:58.447 --> 29:59.322
[knocks]

30:00.864 --> 30:02.198
Hi!

30:02.238 --> 30:03.073
Hey.

30:03.114 --> 30:03.906
Come on.

30:03.948 --> 30:05.781
Okay. One second.

30:13.489 --> 30:16.114
Whew! I feel likeI just ran a marathon,

30:16.114 --> 30:17.781
and that was justthe lunch rush.

30:17.822 --> 30:19.864
I'd like to bea Rosie's waitress one day.

30:19.906 --> 30:21.031
Yeah?

30:21.073 --> 30:22.822
Well, you know, I canput in a good word for you.

30:22.864 --> 30:24.280
I kind of knowthe owner.

30:24.280 --> 30:25.322
Ooh.

30:25.364 --> 30:26.364
Whatcha drawing?

30:26.405 --> 30:28.280
I'm trying to draw Violet.

30:28.322 --> 30:29.198
Oh.

30:29.238 --> 30:30.530
Just make sureyou get my good side.

30:30.572 --> 30:32.280
I don't knowhow to draw noses.

30:32.280 --> 30:33.489
Oh, well, here,

30:33.530 --> 30:35.489
let me show youa little trick.

30:37.031 --> 30:38.280
You go like that,

30:38.322 --> 30:39.322
and then... boop!

30:39.364 --> 30:40.364
You try it.

30:43.239 --> 30:44.530
You're a good artist.

30:44.572 --> 30:45.405
Well, thank you.

30:45.447 --> 30:46.822
You're a good artist.

30:46.864 --> 30:47.906
Hey, Megan,

30:47.948 --> 30:49.989
some guyjust delivered these.

30:53.031 --> 30:53.989
They're for you.

30:56.114 --> 30:57.114
Uh...

30:57.156 --> 30:59.073
from my boyfriend.

30:59.114 --> 31:01.948
He's always doingstuff like this.

31:01.948 --> 31:03.656
So, Megan,

31:03.697 --> 31:05.031
tell us all about

31:05.073 --> 31:06.447
the mysterious manin your life.

31:07.822 --> 31:08.989
He's not mysterious.

31:09.031 --> 31:09.989
Well, Ihaven't met him,

31:10.031 --> 31:11.364
and I'm your best friend.

31:11.405 --> 31:12.739
He's just busy.

31:12.781 --> 31:14.447
[Joe]: I've heardall about him.

31:14.447 --> 31:15.614
His name is Philip,

31:15.614 --> 31:18.156
and he's a big-time attorney.

31:19.031 --> 31:20.489
Yeah.

31:20.530 --> 31:22.280
We met at a party.

31:22.322 --> 31:23.405
What's he like?

31:23.447 --> 31:25.697
Violet, I've told youabout Philip before.

31:25.739 --> 31:26.572
I know,

31:26.614 --> 31:28.781
but I'm sureJoe wants to hear.

31:29.656 --> 31:31.906
Yeah, I wanna hear.

31:31.948 --> 31:33.073
What's he like?

31:35.114 --> 31:37.948
Uh, okay, well,he's a really nice guy,

31:37.989 --> 31:39.906
and he is really...

31:39.948 --> 31:41.489
neat.

31:41.530 --> 31:44.114
Not like a neat-freak "neat,"

31:44.156 --> 31:46.073
but just, like, neat.

31:46.114 --> 31:47.739
And he is, uh,

31:47.781 --> 31:49.989
a really healthy eater.

31:50.031 --> 31:50.906
He juices,

31:50.948 --> 31:53.405
um, and he's anexpert polo player,

31:53.447 --> 31:56.447
and he playsa lot of racquetball--

31:56.447 --> 31:57.948
When he's not busy juicing.

31:57.948 --> 31:59.031
[sighs]

32:00.781 --> 32:01.572
Well, read the card.

32:06.239 --> 32:07.572
"Megan,

32:07.614 --> 32:09.989
all that you areis all that I'll ever need.

32:10.031 --> 32:11.073
Love, Your Man in Waiting."

32:12.322 --> 32:13.781
That's deep.

32:13.822 --> 32:14.739
Shakespeare?

32:14.781 --> 32:16.906
I think it's a 1990sR & B song.

32:16.948 --> 32:19.240
Well, it's romantic,

32:19.280 --> 32:21.447
if not original.

32:21.447 --> 32:23.405
Thank you.

32:25.447 --> 32:27.447
It's quitethe extravagant bouquet.

32:27.489 --> 32:29.198
He must really miss you.

32:30.322 --> 32:31.656
What's that supposed to mean?

32:31.697 --> 32:33.989
It's just an observation.

32:34.031 --> 32:35.614
-Huh.-Here you go.

32:35.656 --> 32:38.906
Wait. Rodrigo,what's this?

32:38.948 --> 32:39.906
Shopping list.

32:42.156 --> 32:44.405
Yeah, Matt handlesall the shopping for the café,

32:44.447 --> 32:45.572
along with the repairs,inventory,

32:45.614 --> 32:48.031
invoices,supplies, payroll.

32:48.073 --> 32:49.447
The usual.

32:49.447 --> 32:51.781
But I...I can't do all that.

32:51.781 --> 32:54.073
I don't actually work here.

32:54.114 --> 32:55.322
Well, I talked to Matt,

32:55.364 --> 32:56.781
and he said you're in chargetill he gets back, so...

32:56.781 --> 32:57.614
But...

32:57.656 --> 32:58.697
Hey, don't worry.You'll do fine.

33:00.948 --> 33:03.614
We have a little problemin the kitchen, boss.

33:03.614 --> 33:06.489
A little problem?

33:11.322 --> 33:12.489
What happened?

33:12.530 --> 33:14.614
Dishwasher goes on the fritzabout once a month.

33:14.614 --> 33:17.114
Matt refusesto get a new one.

33:17.156 --> 33:19.280
Well, this isunacceptable,

33:19.280 --> 33:20.989
but I reallydon't have time

33:21.031 --> 33:22.489
to deal with thisright now.

33:22.530 --> 33:24.781
We need to clear something up.

33:24.781 --> 33:25.906
I have a job,

33:25.948 --> 33:27.322
and I am undera lot of pressure

33:27.364 --> 33:28.280
to do that job,

33:28.322 --> 33:30.948
and I didn't come hereto play waitress,

33:30.948 --> 33:33.948
or fix dishwashers,or fill shopping lists,

33:33.948 --> 33:35.614
so I quit!

33:35.614 --> 33:36.864
[Violet]: Well said.

33:36.906 --> 33:37.781
Mmm.

33:39.073 --> 33:40.156
[sighs]

33:41.822 --> 33:43.572
[dishwasher clunks]

33:45.073 --> 33:46.322
Okay...

33:46.364 --> 33:47.822
I don't quit...

33:47.864 --> 33:49.489
yet.

33:49.530 --> 33:50.906
But what am I supposedto do with this?

33:50.948 --> 33:52.198
I'll take a look.

33:52.239 --> 33:53.530
No, thank you.

33:53.572 --> 33:55.322
We got it.

33:55.364 --> 33:56.989
Dottie, who handlesthis sort of thing?

33:57.031 --> 33:58.697
Well, Matt does,

33:58.739 --> 34:00.156
and when he can'thandle it,

34:00.198 --> 34:01.697
he calls Joe.

34:01.739 --> 34:02.739
[Rodrigo]: Dottie,you got customers.

34:02.781 --> 34:04.781
Hold your horses.

34:04.822 --> 34:07.697
Whatever you do,please do it fast.

34:17.114 --> 34:18.239
I should probably...

34:18.280 --> 34:19.530
Please?

34:19.572 --> 34:20.781
Yeah.

34:20.781 --> 34:21.697
Thank you.

34:21.739 --> 34:23.906
Let's go finishour coffee.

34:29.114 --> 34:30.530
Joe Wainwright,

34:30.572 --> 34:32.447
you always couldfix everything.

34:32.447 --> 34:34.114
[sighs]

34:34.114 --> 34:35.906
Most things.

34:35.947 --> 34:36.947
Good.

34:36.947 --> 34:38.906
Because I'mat an impasse.

34:38.947 --> 34:40.530
I have until Monday morning

34:40.572 --> 34:43.114
to convince...a certain someone

34:43.156 --> 34:44.822
to sell her property,

34:44.864 --> 34:45.781
and she doesn't want to budge,

34:45.822 --> 34:47.239
because she doesn't likethe plans.

34:48.614 --> 34:50.197
I'm sorry, that's justnot my area,

34:50.239 --> 34:52.614
but I'm sureyou'll figure it out.

34:53.656 --> 34:55.364
Great. Thanks.

34:57.530 --> 34:59.989
So, do you thinkthe dishwasher will stay fixed?

35:00.031 --> 35:01.447
Yeah, witha little TLC,

35:01.447 --> 35:02.989
she'll pull through.

35:04.031 --> 35:06.031
Why do you thinkit's a "she"?

35:06.073 --> 35:08.280
Your dad calls her Flo.

35:08.280 --> 35:09.614
Flo?

35:09.656 --> 35:11.614
Clever.

35:12.948 --> 35:16.073
So, uh, what do I owe you?

35:16.114 --> 35:17.114
Um...

35:17.156 --> 35:18.530
It's no charge.

35:18.572 --> 35:20.280
Dad!

35:20.280 --> 35:22.114
I beat Rodrigoin Go Fish!

35:22.114 --> 35:23.948
What?

35:23.948 --> 35:25.114
That's impressive.

35:25.156 --> 35:27.447
I don't beat Rodrigoat anything.

35:27.447 --> 35:28.280
It's easy.

35:28.322 --> 35:29.447
Can we go home now?

35:29.447 --> 35:30.697
I need to get readyfor the hayride.

35:30.739 --> 35:32.031
Sure.

35:32.073 --> 35:34.697
Are you comingto the hayride later?

35:35.948 --> 35:36.989
Um...

35:37.031 --> 35:38.364
It's the Apple Festival,

35:38.405 --> 35:39.656
at the Community Center?

35:43.156 --> 35:45.280
Remember?

35:45.322 --> 35:46.822
There's the hayride,

35:46.864 --> 35:48.781
bobbing for apples,and candy apples.

35:48.822 --> 35:50.198
It's so much fun!

35:51.405 --> 35:53.447
You know what,it's been a really long day,

35:53.447 --> 35:54.697
but maybe another time.

35:54.739 --> 35:56.198
Okay.

35:58.989 --> 36:00.948
All right, tell Meganyou say goodbye.

36:00.989 --> 36:02.114
Bye, Megan.

36:02.114 --> 36:04.364
Goodbye, Lily.

36:04.405 --> 36:05.781
Thanks again.

36:05.781 --> 36:07.447
Of course.

36:08.906 --> 36:10.948
All right, let's getthat seatbelt on, kiddo.

36:10.948 --> 36:11.822
Okay, Dad.

36:17.864 --> 36:19.447
Mrs. Figgins?

36:19.447 --> 36:21.781
Hello, this is Megan Quinn...again.

36:21.822 --> 36:23.656
Uh, listen, I don't meanto be a pest,

36:23.697 --> 36:25.572
but I was wondering if, um,

36:25.614 --> 36:26.614
if you haven't eaten,

36:26.614 --> 36:28.989
maybe I could bring yousome dinner.

36:29.031 --> 36:33.240
Yes, I realize it's after 6:00.

36:33.280 --> 36:37.240
No, I didn't realizeyou eat at 5:00.

36:37.280 --> 36:38.364
Uh, well,

36:38.405 --> 36:39.572
maybe I could bring yousome breakfast in the--

36:39.614 --> 36:41.280
[click, dial tone]

36:41.322 --> 36:43.447
Hello?

36:45.447 --> 36:46.656
[sighs]

36:46.697 --> 36:49.239
I am so fired.

37:00.198 --> 37:02.447
Dinner is served.

37:02.489 --> 37:04.989
[cell phone rings]

37:08.364 --> 37:10.073
[dismisses call]

37:12.906 --> 37:13.948
[sighs]

37:13.948 --> 37:16.530
You do realizeI'm not a vegetarian, right?

37:16.572 --> 37:19.280
Dad, as long asI'm taking care of you,

37:19.280 --> 37:20.489
you're going to eathealthy food.

37:20.530 --> 37:21.864
Hmm.

37:21.906 --> 37:24.489
Can I at least havesome ice cream after dinner?

37:24.530 --> 37:25.656
We'll see.

37:25.697 --> 37:26.572
Hmm.

37:31.530 --> 37:32.906
[Matt sighs]

37:32.948 --> 37:34.364
[Megan sighs]

37:34.405 --> 37:35.447
So...

37:35.447 --> 37:38.822
is there anything goodon TV tonight?

37:39.822 --> 37:41.114
You're not going out?

37:41.114 --> 37:43.822
I've had a really hard day.

37:43.864 --> 37:45.739
I just want to sit hereand not think.

37:45.781 --> 37:47.572
So no hayrides?

37:47.614 --> 37:48.781
No.

37:48.781 --> 37:50.281
Hmm.

37:51.489 --> 37:53.864
What's with that look?

37:53.906 --> 37:55.156
Well, Joe's going to be there.

37:55.198 --> 37:56.281
So?

37:56.281 --> 37:58.447
Well, he's really closewith Frances Figgins.

37:58.489 --> 38:00.240
As a matter of fact,

38:00.281 --> 38:03.364
Joe's over there all the timedoing things for her.

38:03.405 --> 38:06.447
I mean, she thinksJoe Wainwright hung the moon.

38:17.322 --> 38:19.822
[♪♪]

38:19.864 --> 38:22.656
[laughter]

38:36.322 --> 38:37.781
It's getting cool out here.

38:37.781 --> 38:40.031
Let's zip you up.

38:43.239 --> 38:44.031
Hi, guys.

38:44.073 --> 38:46.114
Megan!

38:46.156 --> 38:47.489
I'm so gladyou came!

38:47.530 --> 38:49.697
Me too.

38:49.739 --> 38:50.822
Hey.

38:50.864 --> 38:52.822
Hi.

38:52.864 --> 38:54.447
I got a second wind.

38:54.489 --> 38:57.281
I mean, plus, who doesn't lovea good hayride, right?

38:57.281 --> 38:58.281
Yeah.

38:58.322 --> 39:00.614
All right, well,let's get on board.

39:00.656 --> 39:01.906
All right.

39:09.031 --> 39:10.281
Here we go!

39:10.281 --> 39:11.114
[engine starts]

39:11.156 --> 39:12.530
[Joe]: Hold on tight!

39:12.572 --> 39:14.073
Whoa.

39:14.114 --> 39:16.948
[Joe laughs]

39:16.989 --> 39:19.656
All right!

39:19.697 --> 39:22.948
[♪♪]

39:30.281 --> 39:31.781
[laughing]

39:31.781 --> 39:33.114
Sorry.

39:46.364 --> 39:48.489
Dad, we want to gobobbing for apples!

39:48.530 --> 39:50.031
Okay, have fun.

39:50.073 --> 39:52.572
Okay.

39:52.614 --> 39:53.697
Stay together.

39:53.739 --> 39:55.322
All right, Dad!

39:55.364 --> 39:56.781
That was fun,

39:56.822 --> 39:57.989
the hayride?

39:58.031 --> 39:59.281
Yeah, it was.

40:02.073 --> 40:04.906
Hey, can Iask you a favor?

40:04.948 --> 40:07.572
Depends.

40:07.614 --> 40:09.906
I was just wonderingif you'd come with me

40:09.948 --> 40:12.864
to go seeMrs. Figgins tomorrow.

40:12.906 --> 40:14.614
Why's that?

40:14.614 --> 40:16.948
I just thoughtit'd be fun

40:16.948 --> 40:18.614
to visit here whileI'm here, you know?

40:18.614 --> 40:20.906
Like we used towhen we were kids.

40:20.948 --> 40:21.989
Rumor has it

40:22.031 --> 40:24.447
you've alreadybeen over to see her.

40:25.572 --> 40:26.948
Wait, how did you...?

40:28.322 --> 40:29.614
Oh, right...

40:29.656 --> 40:33.447
[together]: Small towns.

40:33.447 --> 40:35.073
Listen, she justreally likes you,

40:35.114 --> 40:36.656
and she won't take my calls.

40:36.697 --> 40:40.114
Why won't shetake your calls?

40:40.156 --> 40:43.281
My company purchaseda few hundred acres

40:43.322 --> 40:44.739
around Sapphire Lake

40:44.781 --> 40:46.198
for a new retaildevelopment.

40:46.239 --> 40:47.447
We can't break ground

40:47.489 --> 40:49.114
because we needMrs. Figgins' land,

40:49.114 --> 40:51.948
and she refusesto sell to us.

40:51.948 --> 40:55.489
Without her property,the deal is dead.

40:55.530 --> 40:58.281
Your "certain someone?"

40:59.281 --> 41:00.614
Yeah.

41:04.281 --> 41:07.281
So you want me to help you

41:07.322 --> 41:09.447
force a poor old ladyout of her home?

41:09.447 --> 41:12.322
What? No.Of course not.

41:12.364 --> 41:14.281
No one's forcing anyone.

41:14.322 --> 41:16.656
She wants to sellso she can move to Florida.

41:16.697 --> 41:18.114
She just doesn't wantto sell to us,

41:18.156 --> 41:19.530
because she doesn't likethe plans.

41:19.572 --> 41:21.281
If I can pull this off,

41:21.281 --> 41:23.781
I might finally getto realize my dream.

41:23.822 --> 41:26.322
I might actuallyget to be an architect,

41:26.364 --> 41:30.614
and... Frances is goingto end up selling to someone.

41:30.614 --> 41:34.614
Besides, it'll bringhundreds of jobs to Cedarvale.

41:34.656 --> 41:38.489
This is a good thing.Will you please help me?

41:41.322 --> 41:42.697
[Lily]: Dad!

41:45.364 --> 41:47.156
Mom's apple cake.

41:47.198 --> 41:48.614
We have to make it!

41:48.614 --> 41:51.447
"Apple Sampler"?

41:51.489 --> 41:53.156
What's that?

41:53.198 --> 41:55.447
It's something that startedafter you moved away.

41:55.489 --> 41:57.656
A lot of people intown get together,

41:57.697 --> 41:59.656
make their favoriteapple dessert

41:59.697 --> 42:00.781
so the visitors to the Festival

42:00.822 --> 42:02.822
can taste the bestCedarvale has to offer.

42:02.864 --> 42:04.031
Proceeds go to the hospital.

42:04.073 --> 42:06.739
Momma's apple cakewas amazing.

42:06.781 --> 42:07.697
Let's make that!

42:09.530 --> 42:10.572
[sighing] Lilypad, I...

42:10.614 --> 42:13.489
I don't even knowif I have the recipe.

42:15.364 --> 42:16.989
She was the master baker.

42:17.031 --> 42:18.364
I don't knowif I'll do it justice.

42:18.405 --> 42:20.656
We have to make something,

42:21.697 --> 42:23.489
Maybe I could... help.

42:23.530 --> 42:25.906
My mom wasa great baker.

42:25.948 --> 42:27.447
Please, Dad?

42:29.073 --> 42:30.614
Okay, all right.

42:30.656 --> 42:32.156
I'll do it.

42:32.198 --> 42:33.114
We shouldbake something.

42:33.156 --> 42:36.447
I can help youmake an apple pie.

42:36.489 --> 42:37.364
Yeah!

42:37.405 --> 42:38.405
How hard couldthat be, right?

42:39.489 --> 42:41.447
All right, let's go.

42:43.281 --> 42:44.739
[chuckling]

42:44.781 --> 42:46.405
Thanks for comingon the hayride with us.

42:46.447 --> 42:48.322
Thanks for inviting me.

42:48.364 --> 42:49.697
I had a lot of fun.

42:57.447 --> 42:58.530
Megan...

42:58.572 --> 43:00.572
I'll come with you.

43:00.614 --> 43:03.198
You know, Lily's goingto a friend's house tomorrow

43:03.240 --> 43:05.156
during the day, so...

43:05.198 --> 43:07.906
why don't you come bythe farm around noon?

43:07.948 --> 43:09.572
That'd be great.

43:09.614 --> 43:11.198
Thanks.

43:12.281 --> 43:13.281
No problem.

43:13.322 --> 43:14.447
Bye, guys.

43:16.281 --> 43:18.073
Let's go.

43:21.323 --> 43:23.656
[♪♪]

43:30.405 --> 43:31.489
[honks horn]

43:40.656 --> 43:41.489
Hey.

43:41.530 --> 43:42.948
Hey.

43:42.948 --> 43:45.323
I really appreciateyou doing this.

43:45.364 --> 43:46.656
No problem.

43:46.697 --> 43:47.948
But I'm not gonna be part

43:47.989 --> 43:49.323
of your littlebusiness deal, okay?

43:49.364 --> 43:50.948
I'm just coming alongfor the ride.

43:50.989 --> 43:52.156
Okay.

43:52.198 --> 43:53.489
Okay.

44:07.530 --> 44:09.656
You realize you droveright past the Figgins house.

44:09.697 --> 44:10.948
I know.

44:10.948 --> 44:12.948
Just for a minute.

44:12.989 --> 44:15.739
I wanted to see this.

44:16.739 --> 44:18.781
Wow, I'd forgottenhow beautiful it is.

44:21.198 --> 44:22.489
You used to say

44:22.530 --> 44:25.614
this was your favoriteplace on Earth.

44:25.614 --> 44:26.864
Remember?

44:29.781 --> 44:31.239
You have a really good memory.

44:31.281 --> 44:33.864
For things that areworth remembering.

44:36.281 --> 44:38.739
I wanna talk about the future...

44:38.781 --> 44:41.906
our future.

44:41.948 --> 44:44.989
Megan, I'm readyto take things to the--

44:45.031 --> 44:46.114
[cell phone rings]

44:46.156 --> 44:47.447
Um...

44:47.489 --> 44:49.739
hello?

44:51.031 --> 44:51.906
Now?

44:55.697 --> 44:58.447
Okay, I'll be right there.

44:59.697 --> 45:01.114
That was my dad.

45:01.156 --> 45:02.614
I need to get backto the café right away.

45:02.656 --> 45:04.656
Did he say why?

45:04.697 --> 45:06.405
No. He just says

45:06.447 --> 45:07.822
that I need to get thereas soon as possible.

45:07.864 --> 45:09.614
We should go, then.

45:09.656 --> 45:11.114
Okay, let's go.

45:14.447 --> 45:17.614
[♪♪]

45:34.323 --> 45:36.073
I'm gonna checkthe knothole,

45:36.114 --> 45:37.656
just in case.

45:46.614 --> 45:48.822
Nothing.

45:48.864 --> 45:50.530
[chuckles]

45:54.198 --> 45:56.530
I kept your letter.

45:59.031 --> 46:02.323
I wanted to remember.

46:02.364 --> 46:03.530
[sighs]

46:03.572 --> 46:06.073
Remember what I had,what I lost.

46:08.323 --> 46:10.864
You know, you never reallygave me an explanation

46:10.906 --> 46:12.697
for why you broke up with me.

46:12.739 --> 46:14.530
It was a long time ago.

46:14.572 --> 46:17.156
Does that mean you're stillnot going to tell me?

46:19.031 --> 46:21.614
Joe!

46:23.323 --> 46:24.405
Hi!

46:24.447 --> 46:25.614
Hi!

46:25.614 --> 46:27.281
I was just aboutto sit down for lunch.

46:27.323 --> 46:28.489
You care to join me?

46:28.530 --> 46:30.073
Yeah, sure.

46:32.156 --> 46:34.239
Your friend can come too,

46:34.281 --> 46:36.073
if she likes.

46:36.114 --> 46:38.281
Look at that.

46:38.281 --> 46:39.614
Off to a good start.

46:39.656 --> 46:41.530
Oh boy.

46:51.489 --> 46:52.781
Very cleverof you, Ms. Quinn,

46:52.822 --> 46:55.656
to bring Joe alongwith you this time.

46:55.697 --> 46:57.906
You obviously knowhow much I adore him.

46:59.614 --> 47:00.405
Mrs. Figgins,

47:00.447 --> 47:02.781
you knowyou can call me Megan.

47:02.781 --> 47:05.198
I mean, after all, I am stillthe same little girl

47:05.239 --> 47:06.281
that used to come and visit you.

47:06.323 --> 47:08.114
All right, Megan,

47:08.156 --> 47:10.073
and I supposeyou can call me Frances.

47:11.198 --> 47:12.614
But I would appreciate it

47:12.614 --> 47:13.906
if you waituntil we finish lunch

47:13.948 --> 47:16.948
before you try and stealmy house out from under me.

47:20.697 --> 47:21.781
I'm teasing you.

47:21.781 --> 47:24.114
[laughing]

47:24.114 --> 47:25.822
Mark Twain said

47:25.864 --> 47:28.489
humor is one of mankind'sgreatest blessings.

47:29.906 --> 47:32.864
So, Joe, how's Lily?

47:32.906 --> 47:34.031
Oh, she's...she's great.

47:34.073 --> 47:35.530
She's growinglike a beanstalk.

47:35.572 --> 47:36.489
Aw, well, you tell her

47:36.530 --> 47:38.405
that I want to see her soon.

47:38.447 --> 47:39.989
I will.

47:41.364 --> 47:42.989
I still have oneof your drawings, you know.

47:43.031 --> 47:44.323
Really?

47:44.364 --> 47:45.405
Mm-hm.

47:45.447 --> 47:46.447
You were quite good.

47:46.489 --> 47:48.281
You drew a pictureof my house once,

47:48.281 --> 47:49.781
do you remember that?

47:49.781 --> 47:51.405
Yes.

47:51.447 --> 47:52.822
Do you still draw?

47:53.906 --> 47:54.906
Not really.

47:54.948 --> 47:56.364
Oh, that's too bad.

47:56.405 --> 47:58.739
I remember you weregoing to be an architect.

47:59.906 --> 48:01.073
[Joe's cell phone rings]

48:01.114 --> 48:02.906
Oh.

48:02.948 --> 48:05.447
I'm so sorry,I have to get this.

48:05.489 --> 48:07.697
A guy wants to buysome hay.

48:09.572 --> 48:10.656
Hello?

48:10.697 --> 48:12.405
I hear you havesome hungry horses.

48:13.948 --> 48:15.739
Frances, what would it take

48:15.781 --> 48:17.697
to convince youto make a deal with us?

48:17.739 --> 48:19.323
[sighs heavily] I see,

48:19.364 --> 48:21.031
we're back to business.

48:21.073 --> 48:23.031
I still have a job to do.

48:23.073 --> 48:24.114
I told you,

48:24.114 --> 48:26.948
I'm willing to sellto the right buyer,

48:26.948 --> 48:29.405
someone who cares about my lake,

48:29.447 --> 48:31.864
and it's obviouswhoever drew up those plans

48:31.906 --> 48:35.114
has no connection whatsoeverto this land.

48:35.156 --> 48:38.697
I suspect the designernever once

48:38.739 --> 48:42.405
gazed acrossthis majestic lake at sunset,

48:42.447 --> 48:44.239
or watched the shadows fall,

48:44.281 --> 48:47.405
had never seen the geeseappear on the horizon

48:47.447 --> 48:48.948
in a perfect V,

48:48.948 --> 48:51.405
and descend downacross the treetops,

48:51.447 --> 48:54.031
and land gentlyon the water.

48:54.073 --> 48:55.572
Never watcheda mother deer

48:55.614 --> 48:56.864
and her fawn

48:56.906 --> 48:58.198
grazing by the shore,

48:58.240 --> 49:00.447
or heard the frogscroaking at night.

49:00.447 --> 49:03.614
Brick and asphalt?

49:03.614 --> 49:06.906
Fast foodand discount stores?

49:06.948 --> 49:09.906
That is notmy idea of paradise.

49:12.114 --> 49:14.447
Uh, sorry, ladies,

49:14.447 --> 49:16.781
I hate to cut this short,but I have to meet this guy.

49:16.781 --> 49:18.906
Very well.

49:18.948 --> 49:20.489
I understand.

49:20.530 --> 49:23.114
Frances, thank youso much for lunch.

49:23.114 --> 49:24.447
Thanks so much,Frances.

49:24.489 --> 49:25.405
It's my pleasure.

49:27.948 --> 49:29.114
Frances...

49:29.156 --> 49:31.447
would you mindif I came to see you again?

49:31.489 --> 49:32.781
Oh, please do.

49:32.822 --> 49:35.781
But that doesn't mean thatI'm gonna sell to your company.

49:35.781 --> 49:38.697
Well, you can't blame mefor trying.

49:40.114 --> 49:41.739
Goodbye.

49:50.198 --> 49:51.781
Sorry to leave you alone.

49:51.822 --> 49:53.281
We're extra busy.

49:53.281 --> 49:56.031
Oh, that's fine.

49:56.073 --> 49:59.281
You know, you're actuallya pretty good waitress.

49:59.281 --> 50:01.114
Thanks.

50:01.114 --> 50:03.530
You know,the more I'm here,

50:03.572 --> 50:05.572
the more it allcomes back to me.

50:06.739 --> 50:08.781
The memories...

50:09.697 --> 50:11.697
Hanging out here with you

50:11.739 --> 50:13.323
and my mom

50:13.365 --> 50:14.489
when I was little.

50:14.530 --> 50:16.948
We used to sitin that booth right over there,

50:16.989 --> 50:18.948
and she'd help mewith my homework.

50:18.989 --> 50:20.447
She taught me to bake here...

50:22.281 --> 50:24.614
Remember?

50:24.656 --> 50:26.239
[laughing]

50:26.281 --> 50:28.489
[sighs]

50:29.447 --> 50:31.948
She showed me which sideto serve from,

50:31.948 --> 50:34.323
and made sure I never leta customer's coffee cup

50:34.365 --> 50:35.864
get below half full.

50:35.906 --> 50:39.031
She taught meto be nice to people.

50:40.239 --> 50:41.198
And I realize now

50:41.240 --> 50:43.572
they aren't just skillsfor the café,

50:43.614 --> 50:45.572
but they're skills for life.

50:45.614 --> 50:46.989
You know?

50:48.781 --> 50:52.156
Rosie's wasmy mother's dream.

50:52.198 --> 50:53.822
She may have died too young,

50:53.864 --> 50:56.447
but at least she gotto live her dream.

50:56.489 --> 50:57.530
I envy that.

50:57.572 --> 50:59.073
Why?

50:59.114 --> 51:01.530
Because I...

51:01.572 --> 51:03.948
I feel like my dreams

51:03.989 --> 51:07.906
are right there in front of mefor the taking,

51:07.948 --> 51:10.989
and yet they're somehowjust out of reach.

51:12.864 --> 51:13.948
Maybe it's the fact

51:13.948 --> 51:15.656
that our dreamsare hard to reach

51:15.697 --> 51:17.073
that makes themworth reaching for.

51:18.906 --> 51:20.447
[cell phone rings]

51:24.114 --> 51:26.530
It's Joe.

51:27.739 --> 51:29.031
Joe?

51:29.073 --> 51:30.864
Hey there. Hi.

51:30.906 --> 51:31.822
Uh, we've got a little problem.

51:31.864 --> 51:32.906
Okay...

51:32.948 --> 51:35.073
What's a little problem?

51:35.114 --> 51:39.405
Well... Lily and Ibaked an apple...

51:39.447 --> 51:40.656
pie...

51:40.697 --> 51:42.739
At least, I think it was a pie.

51:42.781 --> 51:44.239
Um...

51:44.281 --> 51:46.156
and we were ready to bring it to the Festival,

51:46.198 --> 51:48.281
but I thought the pie had to cool...

51:48.281 --> 51:49.989
and the goat jumped the fenceand ate the pie.

51:50.031 --> 51:51.781
Oh!

51:51.781 --> 51:52.948
Poor Lily.

51:52.989 --> 51:54.405
More like poor goat.

51:54.447 --> 51:58.281
Look, I promised them 12 bales of hay by 5:00 p.m.

51:58.281 --> 52:01.614
and Lily promised thema pie by 6:00, so...

52:01.614 --> 52:02.781
help?

52:02.822 --> 52:04.948
Well, I'm at the café.

52:04.989 --> 52:08.656
Bring Lily, bring the apples,uh, you deliver your hay.

52:08.697 --> 52:09.614
[sighing in relief]

52:09.656 --> 52:11.114
You are a savior.

52:11.156 --> 52:12.240
Thank you so much.

52:12.281 --> 52:14.489
Don't mention it.

52:14.530 --> 52:15.906
Bye.

52:17.031 --> 52:18.073
A goat ate the pie.

52:21.405 --> 52:23.781
It happens.

52:37.198 --> 52:38.697
[chuckling]

52:41.739 --> 52:42.781
Hey.

52:42.822 --> 52:44.948
You know what, Lily?

52:44.948 --> 52:47.697
My mother used to makethe most delicious apple cake.

52:47.739 --> 52:48.864
Your mom? Rosie?

52:48.906 --> 52:49.781
Yeah.

52:49.781 --> 52:50.822
Maybe we should make that?

52:50.864 --> 52:51.781
You and me?

52:51.822 --> 52:52.656
Yeah!

52:52.697 --> 52:54.114
Yeah, okay.

52:54.114 --> 52:55.614
Come here,let's get you an apron.

52:57.365 --> 52:58.614
Okay.

52:58.656 --> 53:01.114
Thank you so much.

53:01.156 --> 53:02.281
You're welcome.

53:02.281 --> 53:03.281
Bye, Dad.

53:03.323 --> 53:05.281
Goodbye.

53:05.281 --> 53:06.656
Have fun, girls.

53:06.697 --> 53:08.114
[Megan]:My mom always said

53:08.114 --> 53:10.031
thatthe first ingredient is love,

53:10.073 --> 53:12.530
when baking.

53:12.572 --> 53:14.073
The trick is,

53:14.114 --> 53:17.073
don't squeeze the eggs.

53:17.114 --> 53:21.323
You want to pull them apart,just like that.

53:21.365 --> 53:23.447
All right,Wainwright apples, going in.

53:23.489 --> 53:26.697
I'm gonna let youstir it all up.

53:26.739 --> 53:28.447
Good.

53:28.447 --> 53:29.822
You want to stir it?-Okay.

53:29.864 --> 53:31.906
[♪♪]

53:31.948 --> 53:34.198
It's hard work, right?

53:41.281 --> 53:42.489
[laughing]

53:42.530 --> 53:44.198
[chuckles]

53:49.697 --> 53:53.781
So the Festival folksliked the cake?

53:53.781 --> 53:56.614
It was hard to tell.

53:56.656 --> 53:57.530
We put it on display,

53:57.572 --> 54:00.365
someone came over,took a bite,

54:00.405 --> 54:01.781
next thing we know,it was gone in five minutes.

54:01.781 --> 54:03.989
So Lily was pleased.

54:04.031 --> 54:05.281
Yes.

54:05.281 --> 54:06.864
Yes, she was very pleased.

54:06.906 --> 54:08.365
Good.

54:12.739 --> 54:14.906
What's wrong?

54:19.447 --> 54:22.739
It's just,Lily is bonding with you,

54:22.781 --> 54:24.405
and it's great...

54:25.614 --> 54:27.323
but you're not goingto be here long,

54:27.365 --> 54:29.739
you know?

54:29.781 --> 54:31.948
Well, I can keep in touch.

54:31.948 --> 54:33.365
It's not the same.

54:33.406 --> 54:35.447
I appreciate the offer.

54:40.114 --> 54:42.156
You are so muchlike your mother.

54:44.530 --> 54:46.114
Thank you.

54:46.114 --> 54:47.073
That's a wonderful compliment.

54:47.114 --> 54:48.739
She was a wonderful person.

54:50.281 --> 54:53.489
You just care so muchabout other people.

54:53.530 --> 54:54.948
So do you.

54:58.530 --> 55:00.489
You know, my mother alwaysthought of you

55:00.530 --> 55:03.031
as the son she never had.

55:14.697 --> 55:16.656
How serious are you?

55:16.697 --> 55:17.948
About...?

55:17.948 --> 55:20.864
Mr. Polo player.

55:22.365 --> 55:23.948
Uh, Philip.

55:23.989 --> 55:24.989
Um...

55:25.031 --> 55:28.656
Well, he'sa really great guy.

55:28.697 --> 55:31.114
He's very ambitious.

55:31.156 --> 55:32.781
He's probably going to runfor office someday.

55:32.781 --> 55:35.240
You didn't answer my question.

55:38.156 --> 55:41.281
He's really good to me.

55:41.281 --> 55:44.489
Still didn't answermy question.

55:44.530 --> 55:46.948
He's... I'm...

55:46.989 --> 55:48.614
Look, it'sgetting late.

55:48.614 --> 55:50.822
Yeah, sure.

55:57.156 --> 55:58.365
Thanksfor the baking help.

55:59.572 --> 56:01.864
Anytime.

56:05.031 --> 56:07.240
[cell phone vibrates]

56:30.948 --> 56:32.697
Cedarvale.

56:35.198 --> 56:38.572
[♪♪]

56:44.281 --> 56:46.989
[Lily]:Let's go! Come on! This way!

56:50.198 --> 56:52.114
Say hi tothe family, okay?

56:56.822 --> 56:57.864
Hey.

56:57.906 --> 56:59.073
Hi.

56:59.114 --> 57:00.114
[Dr. Baker]: Could I haveyour attention, please?

57:00.114 --> 57:01.031
You ready?

57:05.489 --> 57:06.948
Folks, thank you so much

57:06.948 --> 57:09.447
for making this year'sApple Sampler the best ever.

57:09.489 --> 57:13.656
[applause]

57:13.697 --> 57:14.614
And for those of you

57:14.656 --> 57:16.281
who contributed to our hospital,

57:16.281 --> 57:18.864
you are trulythe heartbeat of Cedarvale.

57:18.906 --> 57:20.614
[applause]-I mean...

57:22.822 --> 57:24.781
And now, for this year'sPeople's Choice

57:24.781 --> 57:27.447
for Best Dessert,

57:27.489 --> 57:28.739
the award goes to...

57:30.948 --> 57:33.239
The Wainwright family.

57:33.281 --> 57:34.614
[applause and cheers]

57:34.614 --> 57:36.240
Oh, my gosh!

57:36.281 --> 57:37.114
Yeah!

57:37.156 --> 57:39.281
-What?-We did it.

57:39.281 --> 57:40.281
Thank you, Megan.

57:41.323 --> 57:43.948
I think your motherwould be so proud of you.

57:43.948 --> 57:45.114
Thanks.

57:45.114 --> 57:46.323
I think so too.

57:46.365 --> 57:48.614
Come on,let's go tell Rodrigo!

57:48.614 --> 57:50.365
Okay, all right,all right.

57:52.114 --> 57:53.614
Hey...

57:53.656 --> 57:55.156
wanna come?

57:57.114 --> 57:58.323
You go.

57:58.365 --> 58:00.406
It's a Wainwright moment.

58:15.447 --> 58:18.614
I play golf every Sunday,Ms. Quinn.

58:18.614 --> 58:20.281
It relaxes me.

58:20.323 --> 58:22.697
But today, I'm not relaxed.

58:22.739 --> 58:24.281
Now, why do you think that is?

58:24.281 --> 58:26.948
Well, you said it rained...

58:26.989 --> 58:28.864
That's the least of it, Ms. Quinn.

58:28.906 --> 58:30.614
Try again.

58:30.614 --> 58:32.447
You're worried aboutthe Sapphire Lake project?

58:32.489 --> 58:33.739
Exactly.

58:33.781 --> 58:35.198
Now, I got in six holes,

58:35.239 --> 58:37.114
and I was five over par.

58:37.114 --> 58:38.447
I'm a scratch golfer,Ms. Quinn,

58:38.489 --> 58:39.781
so life is not good.

58:39.781 --> 58:41.948
Well, at leastnow you can relax

58:41.948 --> 58:44.114
and go back to enjoyingthe rest of your Sunday.

58:44.156 --> 58:45.281
I'm back at my office.

58:45.323 --> 58:46.989
Who relaxes at work?

58:47.031 --> 58:48.781
You do remember work, Ms. Quinn?

58:48.822 --> 58:50.489
Now, tell me,

58:50.530 --> 58:53.365
what is happening with this Mrs. Figgins?

58:53.406 --> 58:55.281
Uh, she's beinga little difficult.

58:55.323 --> 58:56.781
Well, that's why I gave you this job.

58:56.822 --> 58:58.614
You're supposed to be able to handle difficult,

58:58.614 --> 59:00.281
help her overcome her reservations

59:00.323 --> 59:01.614
and get the deal done.

59:01.656 --> 59:03.240
Now, you do your job,

59:03.281 --> 59:04.781
or else you'll be lookingfor a new one.

59:04.822 --> 59:05.906
[beeping]

59:05.948 --> 59:07.114
[muttering] Great.

59:07.156 --> 59:08.447
Oh...

59:08.447 --> 59:09.406
Hey, Matt!

59:09.447 --> 59:10.864
Hey!

59:10.906 --> 59:11.822
Good morning!

59:11.864 --> 59:14.739
Dad, what are you doing here?

59:14.781 --> 59:16.240
Well, I got tiredof sitting around the house,

59:16.281 --> 59:18.447
so I thought I'd justcome by and, uh...

59:18.489 --> 59:19.697
do a little cleaning?

59:21.156 --> 59:24.031
Don't worry,I'm not gonna overdo it.

59:24.073 --> 59:25.906
[chuckling] Look at you.

59:25.948 --> 59:29.489
Oh, your mother'd begrinning from ear to ear.

59:29.530 --> 59:30.697
Hey, Matt,how you feelin'?

59:30.739 --> 59:32.198
Like a manwith a busted foot.

59:32.240 --> 59:33.822
Well, you're backin the nick of time, boss.

59:33.864 --> 59:35.031
Megan here

59:35.073 --> 59:36.156
was just about to runthis place into the ground.

59:36.198 --> 59:39.031
Oh, stop it,she did just fine.

59:39.073 --> 59:39.948
So it seems.

59:39.948 --> 59:41.614
Well, welcome back.I gotta go.

59:41.614 --> 59:43.281
Where are you going?I just got here.

59:43.281 --> 59:45.198
I have a meetingto go to.

59:45.240 --> 59:46.281
I'll see you later.

59:46.323 --> 59:47.697
A meeting?

59:47.739 --> 59:49.614
On Sunday?

01:00:01.031 --> 01:00:02.447
This one's perfect.

01:00:02.447 --> 01:00:03.614
Dad and I are goingto make applesauce.

01:00:03.614 --> 01:00:06.031
Just don't letthe goats know, okay?

01:00:06.073 --> 01:00:06.948
[chuckles]

01:00:09.781 --> 01:00:13.114
I thought you weresupposed to leave by noon.

01:00:13.114 --> 01:00:15.281
Yeah.

01:00:15.281 --> 01:00:18.281
I'm headed out to see Francesagain this afternoon.

01:00:18.323 --> 01:00:19.448
I have no choice.

01:00:19.489 --> 01:00:20.614
If I can't get her to signby tomorrow morning,

01:00:20.614 --> 01:00:21.614
I'm out of a job.

01:00:23.156 --> 01:00:25.156
Well...

01:00:25.198 --> 01:00:26.697
You want me to come with you?

01:00:26.739 --> 01:00:27.572
No.

01:00:27.614 --> 01:00:29.739
I just...

01:00:29.781 --> 01:00:30.781
Anyway, I gotta get going.

01:00:31.989 --> 01:00:32.948
Hey, you okay?

01:00:32.948 --> 01:00:35.114
Yeah, I'm fine.

01:00:35.156 --> 01:00:37.198
See ya.

01:00:38.448 --> 01:00:41.114
Megan, hey...

01:00:41.156 --> 01:00:43.614
I know whenyou're not okay.

01:00:43.614 --> 01:00:45.697
I always have.

01:00:45.739 --> 01:00:47.781
Talk to me.

01:00:47.781 --> 01:00:49.614
[sighs heavily]

01:00:49.614 --> 01:00:51.281
Am I doingthe right thing,

01:00:51.323 --> 01:00:53.656
with Frances?

01:00:53.697 --> 01:00:55.948
I mean,I'm not sure anymore.

01:00:55.948 --> 01:00:56.822
Why aren't you sure?

01:00:56.864 --> 01:01:00.281
Because it doesn't feel right.

01:01:00.281 --> 01:01:03.781
When I was little,Frances was so kind to me.

01:01:03.822 --> 01:01:07.281
She encouraged me,and believed in me.

01:01:07.281 --> 01:01:08.448
And now allI can think about

01:01:08.489 --> 01:01:09.864
is getting herto do what I want

01:01:09.906 --> 01:01:11.697
so I can getsome promotion

01:01:11.739 --> 01:01:14.281
and advance my career.

01:01:14.281 --> 01:01:15.697
Is that wrong?

01:01:15.739 --> 01:01:17.281
You know...

01:01:17.281 --> 01:01:19.323
I think,sometimes in life,

01:01:19.365 --> 01:01:21.614
we put on blinders,

01:01:21.614 --> 01:01:23.781
and we think there's onlytwo solutions to a problem.

01:01:23.781 --> 01:01:24.864
What do you mean?

01:01:24.906 --> 01:01:25.948
Well, look,you think

01:01:25.989 --> 01:01:27.156
that Frances eithersells you the property

01:01:27.198 --> 01:01:29.156
or she says no,and the project's dead.

01:01:29.198 --> 01:01:30.948
Yeah, that pretty muchsums it up.

01:01:30.948 --> 01:01:32.572
Well, what if there wasanother option?

01:01:32.614 --> 01:01:34.864
A third option?

01:01:34.906 --> 01:01:35.864
Yeah.

01:01:35.906 --> 01:01:36.697
What?

01:01:36.739 --> 01:01:38.906
Well, I don't know.

01:01:38.948 --> 01:01:40.156
But...

01:01:40.198 --> 01:01:42.198
what I've found isthat when you admit

01:01:42.240 --> 01:01:44.323
there could beanother solution,

01:01:44.365 --> 01:01:46.281
one ends up showing up.

01:01:48.781 --> 01:01:51.948
I'd better get going.Frances is expecting me.

01:01:51.948 --> 01:01:52.864
Bye, Lily.

01:01:52.906 --> 01:01:54.156
Bye, Megan.

01:01:54.198 --> 01:01:55.031
See you later.

01:01:55.948 --> 01:01:56.864
For Frances.

01:01:56.906 --> 01:01:59.614
She loves apples.

01:01:59.656 --> 01:02:00.614
Good luck!

01:02:00.656 --> 01:02:02.739
Thanks.

01:02:11.240 --> 01:02:12.781
So, Megan's going home soon,

01:02:12.822 --> 01:02:13.864
huh, Dad?

01:02:13.906 --> 01:02:15.365
That's right.

01:02:18.781 --> 01:02:19.948
Are you going to miss her?

01:02:21.448 --> 01:02:23.239
A little.

01:02:23.281 --> 01:02:25.906
I miss Mommy,

01:02:25.948 --> 01:02:28.448
even though I was little.

01:02:28.448 --> 01:02:30.240
Sometimes I wishI could tell her that.

01:02:31.781 --> 01:02:32.614
So...

01:02:32.656 --> 01:02:34.073
if you're going to miss Megan,

01:02:34.114 --> 01:02:35.323
I think you should tell her,

01:02:35.365 --> 01:02:36.614
or she'll never know.

01:02:39.323 --> 01:02:40.656
[chuckles]

01:02:44.572 --> 01:02:45.406
You know what,

01:02:45.448 --> 01:02:47.281
I thinkyou're right.

01:02:47.281 --> 01:02:48.948
We're done apple picking.

01:02:48.948 --> 01:02:50.448
All right?-Okay.

01:02:54.281 --> 01:02:57.198
[♪♪]

01:03:02.114 --> 01:03:04.156
I love this view.

01:03:04.198 --> 01:03:06.906
That drawing you oncemade of my house?

01:03:06.948 --> 01:03:08.073
I still have it,

01:03:08.114 --> 01:03:10.281
framed,near my mantle.

01:03:10.323 --> 01:03:13.281
Oh, wow,I'm flattered.

01:03:13.281 --> 01:03:16.906
Ah, you were alwaystalented, Megan.

01:03:16.948 --> 01:03:17.989
Always.

01:03:19.323 --> 01:03:21.781
Oh, it's stillso beautiful, isn't it?

01:03:21.822 --> 01:03:24.781
The reflection of leaveson the water?

01:03:24.781 --> 01:03:26.323
Yeah, it is.

01:03:26.365 --> 01:03:28.948
I used to loveto come down here as a girl

01:03:28.948 --> 01:03:30.073
and skip stones.

01:03:30.114 --> 01:03:31.406
Oh, me too.

01:03:31.448 --> 01:03:32.906
Joe and Iused to do that.

01:03:32.948 --> 01:03:34.406
Joe's a good man.

01:03:35.530 --> 01:03:37.240
Yeah, he is.

01:03:37.281 --> 01:03:38.365
We all thought

01:03:38.406 --> 01:03:40.198
you were destinedfor one another,

01:03:40.240 --> 01:03:41.656
the whole town.

01:03:41.697 --> 01:03:43.114
Well, Ithought so too,

01:03:43.114 --> 01:03:44.989
but then he...

01:03:45.031 --> 01:03:46.198
broke up with me,

01:03:46.240 --> 01:03:47.781
just like that.

01:03:47.781 --> 01:03:50.489
Ah yes,the "Dear Megan" letter.

01:03:50.530 --> 01:03:52.948
Joe told me about it.

01:03:52.989 --> 01:03:55.448
He came out to my housethe day he mailed it.

01:03:55.489 --> 01:03:57.697
Oh, he waspractically inconsolable.

01:03:57.739 --> 01:03:59.489
Inconsolable?

01:04:00.822 --> 01:04:01.948
He... he wrote me

01:04:01.989 --> 01:04:03.948
and told me he didn'twant to see me anymore.

01:04:03.948 --> 01:04:05.948
Your Joe was just a young man,

01:04:05.989 --> 01:04:07.989
but he was smart enough to know

01:04:08.031 --> 01:04:10.448
that he had to let you goand chase your dreams,

01:04:10.489 --> 01:04:12.822
and he was so afraidthat you'd resent him,

01:04:12.864 --> 01:04:15.281
so he tolda little white lie

01:04:15.323 --> 01:04:17.948
to make it easier for you.

01:04:17.948 --> 01:04:20.697
But I was justgoing off to college.

01:04:20.739 --> 01:04:22.781
We could have found a wayto make it work.

01:04:22.781 --> 01:04:25.323
Joe wanted to give youyour freedom,

01:04:25.365 --> 01:04:27.323
so he made a choice.

01:04:27.365 --> 01:04:29.948
Now, maybe you could havemade it work,

01:04:29.989 --> 01:04:32.614
and maybe not.

01:04:32.656 --> 01:04:34.281
And now it's too late.

01:04:34.323 --> 01:04:37.448
You have a special placein Joe's heart, Megan,

01:04:37.448 --> 01:04:40.198
and no matter what happensfrom this point forward,

01:04:40.240 --> 01:04:42.489
you always will.

01:04:42.530 --> 01:04:46.198
A first loveis a forever love.

01:04:54.572 --> 01:04:57.697
Well, I had a lovely time.

01:04:57.739 --> 01:04:59.906
Me too.

01:04:59.948 --> 01:05:01.906
Frances...

01:05:01.948 --> 01:05:03.781
can I ask you a question?

01:05:03.781 --> 01:05:05.281
You want to knowwhat it's going to take

01:05:05.323 --> 01:05:07.365
to convince me to sell my houseto your company.

01:05:09.448 --> 01:05:12.198
Look around you.

01:05:13.489 --> 01:05:15.739
What do you see?

01:05:18.739 --> 01:05:20.073
Beauty.

01:05:20.114 --> 01:05:21.530
Peace.

01:05:21.572 --> 01:05:23.781
It really is a special place.

01:05:23.822 --> 01:05:24.906
Yes,

01:05:24.948 --> 01:05:26.822
and the plan that yourcompany has presented

01:05:26.864 --> 01:05:30.281
doesn't respect the beautyof this special place.

01:05:30.281 --> 01:05:32.614
Now, if you cancome up with a way

01:05:32.656 --> 01:05:34.822
to keep the beautyof this lake alive,

01:05:34.864 --> 01:05:36.406
then maybe we can do business.

01:05:36.448 --> 01:05:38.781
But how?

01:05:38.781 --> 01:05:39.739
The plans are set.

01:05:39.781 --> 01:05:41.073
they have been for months.

01:05:41.114 --> 01:05:42.948
Put your heart into it.

01:05:42.948 --> 01:05:45.156
Goodbye.

01:05:46.073 --> 01:05:47.989
Bye.

01:05:52.240 --> 01:05:53.906
[cell phone vibrates]

01:05:57.781 --> 01:05:58.906
Hello?

01:05:58.948 --> 01:06:00.114
Megan, you need to come right away.

01:06:00.114 --> 01:06:01.781
Yeah, Flo'sbeen acting up again,

01:06:01.781 --> 01:06:03.073
and your dad's not around.

01:06:03.114 --> 01:06:04.281
Flo?

01:06:04.323 --> 01:06:05.572
The dishwasher!

01:06:05.614 --> 01:06:08.114
All right, I'll be right there.

01:06:08.114 --> 01:06:09.614
And maybe you should call Joe.

01:06:11.781 --> 01:06:13.448
Okay.

01:06:20.989 --> 01:06:23.948
Hey, Dottie, is it bad?

01:06:23.948 --> 01:06:25.781
Did you call Joe?

01:06:25.822 --> 01:06:28.697
No need to.

01:06:32.240 --> 01:06:33.031
Joe?

01:06:33.073 --> 01:06:35.739
Hey, Megs.

01:06:38.406 --> 01:06:40.114
Um...

01:06:43.073 --> 01:06:45.114
Megan... [clearing throat]

01:06:45.114 --> 01:06:46.448
we've known each othera long time...

01:06:48.530 --> 01:06:52.114
and when I saw youthe other day,

01:06:52.156 --> 01:06:54.114
when you bumped into mein the street,

01:06:54.114 --> 01:06:57.864
I needed to tell you that

01:06:57.906 --> 01:06:59.448
I felt something.

01:06:59.448 --> 01:07:01.031
Mmm.

01:07:02.281 --> 01:07:05.365
...and it made me realize

01:07:05.406 --> 01:07:09.031
that the feelingsI've had for you a long time ago

01:07:09.073 --> 01:07:10.614
have never gone away.

01:07:12.948 --> 01:07:14.989
Megan...

01:07:18.614 --> 01:07:20.239
I don't want to lose you again.

01:07:21.281 --> 01:07:22.448
And...

01:07:22.490 --> 01:07:23.490
[door opens]Megan?

01:07:27.448 --> 01:07:28.948
Philip?

01:07:28.989 --> 01:07:30.198
I was hopingyou'd be here.

01:07:32.031 --> 01:07:33.864
What are you doing here?

01:07:33.906 --> 01:07:35.948
I couldn't stand itany longer.

01:07:35.989 --> 01:07:37.073
I had to see you.

01:07:37.114 --> 01:07:40.864
Megan, honey,

01:07:40.906 --> 01:07:43.281
I don't know whatthe future holds for us,

01:07:43.281 --> 01:07:46.114
but I think we shouldchoose each other,

01:07:46.156 --> 01:07:49.198
and just figure it outas we go.

01:07:49.239 --> 01:07:51.781
So...

01:07:51.781 --> 01:07:54.365
Megan Anne Quinn...

01:07:56.697 --> 01:07:58.114
will you be my wife?

01:08:05.781 --> 01:08:07.448
Uh...

01:08:08.448 --> 01:08:09.323
Megan...

01:08:12.365 --> 01:08:14.697
I-I'm sorry.

01:08:14.739 --> 01:08:16.697
Congratulations.

01:08:19.948 --> 01:08:21.656
Joe, wait!

01:08:28.948 --> 01:08:31.822
Philip, please stand up.

01:08:39.198 --> 01:08:40.448
I'll be back.

01:08:40.448 --> 01:08:41.490
Megan!

01:08:43.198 --> 01:08:44.906
Who's Joe?

01:08:50.323 --> 01:08:52.863
Joe, wait a second.

01:08:52.906 --> 01:08:54.323
Wait!

01:08:55.448 --> 01:08:58.365
You broke upwith me, remember?

01:08:58.406 --> 01:09:00.448
You wrote me a letter,and that was it.

01:09:00.490 --> 01:09:01.529
No explanation,

01:09:01.572 --> 01:09:03.822
and poof, and you weregone from my life.

01:09:03.863 --> 01:09:05.738
[sighs in exasperation]

01:09:05.781 --> 01:09:07.156
I thought we werebest friends, Joe.

01:09:07.198 --> 01:09:10.529
I thought we were goingto build a life together.

01:09:10.572 --> 01:09:13.156
I didn't want to standin the way of your dream.

01:09:13.198 --> 01:09:15.113
So you made a choice for me

01:09:15.113 --> 01:09:19.113
without even talking about it?

01:09:19.156 --> 01:09:20.448
I know why you did it, Joe.

01:09:20.448 --> 01:09:23.656
Frances told me.

01:09:23.697 --> 01:09:24.822
But you were wrong.

01:09:24.863 --> 01:09:27.448
We could havemade it work.

01:09:27.448 --> 01:09:30.031
We could have made it workbecause I loved you,

01:09:30.073 --> 01:09:31.448
and I know you loved me--

01:09:31.490 --> 01:09:32.822
Okay,all right.

01:09:32.863 --> 01:09:35.281
Go back inside, okay?

01:09:35.281 --> 01:09:38.113
Philip's waiting.

01:09:38.156 --> 01:09:39.323
Don't do this again.

01:09:39.365 --> 01:09:40.781
Don't push me away.

01:09:40.781 --> 01:09:42.781
We're living twodifferent lives, Megan.

01:09:42.781 --> 01:09:46.198
Your life is back in Chicagowith Philip.

01:09:46.238 --> 01:09:49.948
My life ishere with Lily.

01:09:49.988 --> 01:09:51.988
I guess I...

01:09:54.323 --> 01:09:57.822
I thought we couldget back what we once had.

01:10:04.156 --> 01:10:06.989
I don't knowwhat I was thinking.

01:10:07.031 --> 01:10:09.031
[car door opens]

01:10:09.073 --> 01:10:11.697
[Megan]:Joe...

01:10:11.739 --> 01:10:13.073
Megan?

01:10:18.406 --> 01:10:21.989
Philip, we need to talk.

01:10:25.406 --> 01:10:26.365
All right, thanks!Come again!

01:10:26.406 --> 01:10:27.365
[man calls]:Thanks, Matt!

01:10:27.406 --> 01:10:28.406
[chuckling]:Yeah. See ya.

01:10:28.448 --> 01:10:30.198
Always a pleasure.

01:10:33.073 --> 01:10:35.614
Let me know when youget back to Chicago.

01:10:35.656 --> 01:10:37.240
You're a great guy.

01:10:49.156 --> 01:10:50.656
Ah.

01:10:50.697 --> 01:10:52.281
Seemed like a nice enough fella.

01:10:53.948 --> 01:10:54.781
[sighs heavily]

01:10:54.822 --> 01:10:56.114
We broke up.

01:10:56.156 --> 01:10:57.198
Well, good.

01:10:57.239 --> 01:10:58.614
Then I don't have to payfor the wedding.

01:11:00.448 --> 01:11:01.240
[chuckles]

01:11:01.281 --> 01:11:02.281
Come on, I'm kidding.

01:11:06.198 --> 01:11:07.781
You wanna talk about it?

01:11:07.781 --> 01:11:10.406
No, thank you.

01:11:10.448 --> 01:11:12.822
Dad, if you don'tneed me here,

01:11:12.864 --> 01:11:15.323
I think I'd like to go home.

01:11:15.365 --> 01:11:17.530
I need to start workingon my résumé.

01:11:17.572 --> 01:11:20.323
Sure, I thinkwe can manage somehow.

01:11:22.614 --> 01:11:24.114
Ooh, before you go,

01:11:24.114 --> 01:11:26.781
I was in the back officecleaning this morning,

01:11:26.781 --> 01:11:28.697
and I found this.

01:11:30.281 --> 01:11:31.198
What is it?

01:11:31.240 --> 01:11:32.240
Have a look.

01:11:38.406 --> 01:11:40.240
Huh?

01:11:40.281 --> 01:11:41.822
Remember those?

01:11:41.864 --> 01:11:45.531
No, your mother was planningon making a new menu,

01:11:45.572 --> 01:11:47.656
and she wanted to useone of your drawings

01:11:47.697 --> 01:11:48.989
as the cover.

01:11:50.281 --> 01:11:51.448
Of course, she died

01:11:51.448 --> 01:11:54.406
before she could putthe plan into motion.

01:11:56.948 --> 01:11:59.448
Yeah, she was alwaysyour biggest fan.

01:12:07.031 --> 01:12:09.948
[♪♪]

01:12:13.198 --> 01:12:15.198
The third option!

01:12:16.240 --> 01:12:17.948
Dad, thank you!

01:12:17.948 --> 01:12:19.989
Oh, you're the best.

01:12:21.281 --> 01:12:22.614
Uh, don't mention it...

01:12:22.614 --> 01:12:23.948
I guess.

01:12:23.948 --> 01:12:25.614
The third what?

01:12:25.656 --> 01:12:27.864
[♪♪]

01:12:53.406 --> 01:12:55.989
[rain pouring]

01:12:56.031 --> 01:12:58.156
[♪♪]

01:13:18.697 --> 01:13:20.906
[birds tweeting]

01:13:31.906 --> 01:13:33.906
[muffled cell phone ringing]

01:13:40.781 --> 01:13:41.822
Hello?

01:13:41.864 --> 01:13:43.114
[whispering] Megan!

01:13:43.156 --> 01:13:44.572
I've been tryingto reach you all morning.

01:13:44.614 --> 01:13:45.490
Do you know what today is?

01:13:45.531 --> 01:13:46.697
No, what?

01:13:46.739 --> 01:13:48.781
Today's Monday,which means deadline day?

01:13:48.781 --> 01:13:51.656
Oh, no. Shoot!

01:13:52.572 --> 01:13:53.614
My deadline.

01:13:53.614 --> 01:13:55.114
It's less than an hour away.

01:13:55.156 --> 01:13:57.198
Why do you think I've beentrying to reach you all morning?

01:13:57.239 --> 01:13:59.614
Mr. St. Clair's on his way to Cedarvale right now,

01:13:59.656 --> 01:14:01.281
and he's not happy.

01:14:01.281 --> 01:14:03.781
Oh, no.Okay, okay, I'm on it.

01:14:03.822 --> 01:14:05.572
Uh, I'll call you later.

01:14:05.614 --> 01:14:06.531
[beeping off]

01:14:08.281 --> 01:14:09.114
I'm heading out, Dad!

01:14:09.156 --> 01:14:10.781
Good luck!

01:14:22.406 --> 01:14:26.989
So, if you'll just signat the bottom...

01:14:27.031 --> 01:14:29.656
And what if I don'tsign, Mr. St. Clair?

01:14:29.697 --> 01:14:31.948
Mrs. Figgins...may I call you Frances?

01:14:31.948 --> 01:14:33.406
No.

01:14:34.448 --> 01:14:35.614
Mrs. Figgins,

01:14:35.656 --> 01:14:39.323
Stoneland Properties ownsall of the surrounding land,

01:14:39.365 --> 01:14:41.781
so there will be no more buyers.

01:14:41.822 --> 01:14:44.365
Now, if you continueto hold out,

01:14:44.406 --> 01:14:46.531
well, we'll be forcedto break ground

01:14:46.572 --> 01:14:48.656
on the portion of landthat we do own,

01:14:48.697 --> 01:14:49.948
and, unfortunately,

01:14:49.948 --> 01:14:52.323
it will getpretty noisy around here,

01:14:52.365 --> 01:14:55.948
and this is a sweetheartof a deal, Mrs. Figgins.

01:14:55.989 --> 01:14:57.614
But if we're forcedto delay much longer,

01:14:57.614 --> 01:14:59.697
it might notbe so sweet.

01:14:59.739 --> 01:15:03.156
Now, this really isthe only option.

01:15:09.031 --> 01:15:11.031
[car honks]

01:15:14.531 --> 01:15:15.948
Wait!

01:15:15.948 --> 01:15:17.031
Don't sign anything.

01:15:17.989 --> 01:15:18.948
Don't signanything.

01:15:18.989 --> 01:15:21.239
Ms. Quinn?

01:15:21.281 --> 01:15:22.114
What do you think you're doing?

01:15:22.114 --> 01:15:23.490
Just bear with me, please.

01:15:23.531 --> 01:15:24.822
Bear with you?

01:15:24.864 --> 01:15:27.739
No. No, you had your chance,and you missed your deadline.

01:15:27.781 --> 01:15:28.739
That's why I'm here.

01:15:28.781 --> 01:15:29.739
No,not yet.

01:15:29.781 --> 01:15:31.031
I still have...

01:15:31.073 --> 01:15:32.365
four minutes.

01:15:32.406 --> 01:15:33.406
No, Ms. Quinn,

01:15:33.448 --> 01:15:34.989
you no longer havenegotiating authority

01:15:35.031 --> 01:15:35.906
on this project.

01:15:35.948 --> 01:15:37.114
Now, a deal is on the table.

01:15:37.156 --> 01:15:39.239
On the table,perhaps,

01:15:39.281 --> 01:15:40.989
but the penis still in my hand.

01:15:41.031 --> 01:15:43.114
I want to hear what Meganhas come up with.

01:15:43.114 --> 01:15:45.614
Mrs. Figgins,the plans are all set.

01:15:45.614 --> 01:15:47.406
We're getting readyto break ground.

01:15:47.448 --> 01:15:48.490
It's really too latefor any changes.

01:15:48.531 --> 01:15:49.739
Excuse me,Mr. St. Clair,

01:15:49.781 --> 01:15:50.989
but Mrs. Figgins' property

01:15:51.031 --> 01:15:52.323
sits dead center

01:15:52.365 --> 01:15:53.614
of the proposeddevelopment.

01:15:53.656 --> 01:15:54.781
Without her land,

01:15:54.781 --> 01:15:56.448
there's no waythe local planning commission

01:15:56.490 --> 01:15:57.864
will ever approve the project,

01:15:57.906 --> 01:15:58.822
and if she'snot budging,

01:15:58.864 --> 01:15:59.739
we don'thave a choice

01:15:59.781 --> 01:16:01.073
but to look atother options.

01:16:01.114 --> 01:16:02.281
Not budging?

01:16:02.323 --> 01:16:04.240
She was about to signbefore you got here.

01:16:04.281 --> 01:16:06.614
Well, now I've hada sudden change of heart.

01:16:13.614 --> 01:16:16.156
I want to hearwhat Megan has come up with.

01:16:21.114 --> 01:16:22.031
This better be good.

01:16:24.739 --> 01:16:25.531
Okay.

01:16:25.572 --> 01:16:26.948
Last night,

01:16:26.989 --> 01:16:28.073
I was thinkingthis whole thing over,

01:16:28.114 --> 01:16:29.948
and I realizedthat Frances is not being

01:16:29.948 --> 01:16:31.864
at all unreasonable.

01:16:31.906 --> 01:16:33.031
Of course not.

01:16:33.073 --> 01:16:34.948
All she wantsis to ensure

01:16:34.948 --> 01:16:36.531
that this stunninglybeautiful place,

01:16:36.572 --> 01:16:38.531
where she's spenther entire life,

01:16:38.572 --> 01:16:39.572
remains that way,

01:16:39.614 --> 01:16:41.948
and I think thatwith a little creativity,

01:16:41.948 --> 01:16:43.406
we can both get what we want.

01:16:43.448 --> 01:16:45.781
We can builda profitable development

01:16:45.822 --> 01:16:47.614
that respects the environment.

01:16:47.656 --> 01:16:49.406
Interesting.

01:16:55.323 --> 01:16:58.781
No, no, no, no, no,this is far too much green.

01:16:58.781 --> 01:17:00.781
Are these trails?

01:17:00.822 --> 01:17:02.448
These treesare all supposed to be removed.

01:17:02.448 --> 01:17:03.656
But theydon't have to be.

01:17:03.697 --> 01:17:05.948
I've adjusted the footprintof the development,

01:17:05.989 --> 01:17:08.323
but the square footageremains exactly the same.

01:17:08.365 --> 01:17:12.073
I've arranged the restaurants

01:17:12.114 --> 01:17:14.781
so they getthe best views of the lake,

01:17:14.781 --> 01:17:16.948
and I sketched ingreen footpaths

01:17:16.989 --> 01:17:18.948
from the parking structureto the retail area,

01:17:18.989 --> 01:17:20.448
and I put ina playscape for kids

01:17:20.448 --> 01:17:22.114
by the water.

01:17:22.156 --> 01:17:24.114
I think we can makethis development

01:17:24.114 --> 01:17:25.989
a place where customerswant to linger,

01:17:26.031 --> 01:17:28.573
and if we can do that,

01:17:28.614 --> 01:17:30.114
they'll wantto come back,

01:17:30.156 --> 01:17:31.323
and in the long run,

01:17:31.365 --> 01:17:32.864
if we create a space

01:17:32.906 --> 01:17:33.948
that peoplewant to return to

01:17:33.948 --> 01:17:35.781
again and again,

01:17:35.781 --> 01:17:37.531
that means bigger profits.

01:17:40.323 --> 01:17:42.448
I'm really proud of you.

01:17:42.448 --> 01:17:44.490
You have done a beautiful job.

01:17:46.822 --> 01:17:48.614
Just to be clear, Mrs. Figgins,

01:17:48.614 --> 01:17:49.781
you're saying

01:17:49.822 --> 01:17:51.822
that if we go with this plan,

01:17:51.864 --> 01:17:53.989
you might consentto selling your property?

01:17:54.031 --> 01:17:54.822
Yes.

01:17:54.864 --> 01:17:57.114
I could bepersuaded.

01:17:57.156 --> 01:17:58.864
I'm not against development,Mr. St. Clair.

01:17:58.906 --> 01:18:00.656
It just has to bethe right kind.

01:18:06.198 --> 01:18:08.073
Okay, Ms. Quinn.

01:18:09.448 --> 01:18:11.822
Get these plans onthe drawing board.

01:18:11.864 --> 01:18:13.323
We'll see if we canmake this happen.

01:18:13.365 --> 01:18:15.114
I am on it.

01:18:21.864 --> 01:18:23.697
I knewyou had it in you.

01:18:23.739 --> 01:18:24.614
Thank you.

01:18:24.656 --> 01:18:25.573
Do you like it?

01:18:25.614 --> 01:18:27.822
I love it.

01:18:28.781 --> 01:18:30.739
Let me show you.

01:18:30.781 --> 01:18:31.948
Yes.

01:18:31.948 --> 01:18:35.198
[♪♪]

01:18:49.573 --> 01:18:51.656
Hey, there she is.

01:18:51.697 --> 01:18:52.614
Hey, guys.

01:18:52.656 --> 01:18:54.240
Hey, how aboutsome pie, Megan?

01:18:54.281 --> 01:18:55.114
Mmm....

01:18:55.156 --> 01:18:56.239
maybe later.

01:18:56.281 --> 01:18:57.281
Megan!

01:18:57.281 --> 01:18:59.323
Hey, Dad.

01:18:59.365 --> 01:19:00.448
Hey.

01:19:00.490 --> 01:19:03.281
That piece has my namewritten all over it.

01:19:03.281 --> 01:19:05.281
So...

01:19:06.448 --> 01:19:08.697
I'm going to be heading backto Chicago in the morning.

01:19:08.739 --> 01:19:10.448
Huh? So soon?

01:19:10.448 --> 01:19:12.281
I've got to get readyfor my new assignment.

01:19:12.281 --> 01:19:13.822
New assignment?

01:19:14.948 --> 01:19:18.073
I've been chosen to leadthe Sapphire Lake development.

01:19:18.114 --> 01:19:19.448
[gasps] Really?

01:19:19.490 --> 01:19:20.614
Well... well, that's wonderful.

01:19:20.656 --> 01:19:21.697
That means you'll be--

01:19:21.739 --> 01:19:23.781
Moving back to Cedarvale,

01:19:23.822 --> 01:19:25.573
at least forthe foreseeable future.

01:19:25.614 --> 01:19:27.656
Oh, sweetheart,

01:19:27.697 --> 01:19:29.031
I am so proud of you.

01:19:29.073 --> 01:19:31.614
You know,for your mother and me,

01:19:31.614 --> 01:19:34.114
it was never aboutwhat you achieve,

01:19:34.156 --> 01:19:35.531
it was always about who you are.

01:19:36.781 --> 01:19:38.614
Your mother would beso proud of you,

01:19:38.614 --> 01:19:40.239
just like I am.

01:19:40.281 --> 01:19:42.656
Thanks, Dad.

01:19:42.697 --> 01:19:46.073
[♪♪]

01:20:18.448 --> 01:20:19.948
[Megan writes]: "Dear Joe.

01:20:19.948 --> 01:20:24.156
Just in case you're wondering, Philip and I broke up.

01:20:24.198 --> 01:20:25.614
I guess I finally realized

01:20:25.614 --> 01:20:28.281
that my heart wasn't his for the taking,

01:20:28.323 --> 01:20:30.198
because I had already given it away.

01:20:31.281 --> 01:20:35.281
It's been hard coming back home.

01:20:35.281 --> 01:20:36.906
There have been so many reminders

01:20:36.948 --> 01:20:38.365
of things that I had forgotten...

01:20:41.448 --> 01:20:43.614
Reminders of growing up with my family,

01:20:43.614 --> 01:20:45.281
my mother...

01:20:47.114 --> 01:20:50.614
reminders of who I was before I left...

01:20:50.656 --> 01:20:52.781
who I still am.

01:20:54.323 --> 01:20:55.614
Someone once said

01:20:55.614 --> 01:20:59.656
that a first love is a forever love...

01:20:59.697 --> 01:21:03.281
and, Joe, when I think of you, and me,

01:21:03.323 --> 01:21:06.490
and our love story,

01:21:06.531 --> 01:21:09.614
I know truer words were never spoken.

01:21:11.406 --> 01:21:14.822
Yours forever, Megan."

01:21:18.281 --> 01:21:20.614
[♪♪]

01:21:29.822 --> 01:21:32.114
[sighing]

01:21:32.156 --> 01:21:34.864
You really thinkit's true?

01:21:40.406 --> 01:21:43.614
About first lovesbeing forever?

01:21:44.906 --> 01:21:46.114
I do.

01:21:52.323 --> 01:21:56.323
I found your note,in our tree.

01:21:58.198 --> 01:22:00.406
How did you even...?

01:22:01.448 --> 01:22:02.281
Oh, wait,

01:22:02.281 --> 01:22:04.031
of course, Frances.

01:22:05.948 --> 01:22:06.948
I was goingto tell you about it

01:22:06.989 --> 01:22:09.198
after I was safely out of town.

01:22:09.240 --> 01:22:12.031
I figured.

01:22:13.031 --> 01:22:14.989
Um...

01:22:15.031 --> 01:22:17.114
I was sorry to hearthat things didn't work out

01:22:17.114 --> 01:22:19.240
between you and Philip.

01:22:19.281 --> 01:22:21.906
I'm not.

01:22:28.281 --> 01:22:29.822
I, um...

01:22:31.656 --> 01:22:34.073
I have something for you.

01:22:35.031 --> 01:22:36.781
What's this?

01:22:36.822 --> 01:22:39.365
It's a promise ring.

01:22:39.406 --> 01:22:42.781
A promise that's been12 years in the making.

01:22:45.822 --> 01:22:46.989
I love it.

01:22:49.490 --> 01:22:52.739
What exactly is ityou're promising me?

01:22:54.822 --> 01:22:56.114
Just this.

01:22:57.781 --> 01:22:59.073
[♪♪]

01:23:25.822 --> 01:23:27.448
[♪♪]

01:23:29.573 --> 01:23:31.031
Megan!

01:23:31.073 --> 01:23:32.323
Dad!

01:23:35.573 --> 01:23:37.822
[chuckling fondly]

01:23:40.490 --> 01:23:42.490
All right, come on, let's go.

01:23:42.531 --> 01:23:44.739
[♪♪]

01:24:02.114 --> 01:24:04.031
[♪♪]
